WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.479 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:03.479 --> 00:00:22.390 align:middle line:90%


00:00:22.390 --> 00:00:23.870 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA GARR: What is my purpose?

00:00:23.870 --> 00:00:26.590 align:middle line:84%
This is the most asked question
of my radio show callers

00:00:26.590 --> 00:00:29.380 align:middle line:84%
who are trying to make
sense of why we are here.

00:00:29.380 --> 00:00:32.049 align:middle line:10%
This question is also what
started best-selling author

00:00:32.049 --> 00:00:34.060 align:middle line:10%
of the "Way of the
Peaceful Warrior"

00:00:34.060 --> 00:00:36.400 align:middle line:10%
on his journey that
impacted millions.

00:00:36.400 --> 00:00:39.280 align:middle line:10%
Dan Millman, former
world champion gymnast

00:00:39.280 --> 00:00:40.990 align:middle line:10%
and college professor,
he's the author

00:00:40.990 --> 00:00:43.900 align:middle line:10%
of 17 books published
in 29 languages

00:00:43.900 --> 00:00:47.050 align:middle line:10%
and shared across generations
to millions of readers.

00:00:47.050 --> 00:00:48.910 align:middle line:10%
His internationally
best-selling book

00:00:48.910 --> 00:00:53.110 align:middle line:10%
"Way of the Peaceful Warrior"
was adapted to film in 2006.

00:00:53.110 --> 00:00:53.965 align:middle line:90%
Welcome.

00:00:53.965 --> 00:00:55.120 align:middle line:90%
>>DAN MILLMAN: Hi, Lisa.

00:00:55.120 --> 00:00:56.573 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So great
to have you here.

00:00:56.573 --> 00:00:57.740 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLMAN: Great to be here.

00:00:57.740 --> 00:00:58.540 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: So tell me.

00:00:58.540 --> 00:00:59.870 align:middle line:10%
Well, first of all, your book.

00:00:59.870 --> 00:01:00.250 align:middle line:10%
And I read it.

00:01:00.250 --> 00:01:01.050 align:middle line:10%
And I loved it.

00:01:01.050 --> 00:01:03.010 align:middle line:10%
And it's impacted so
many people's lives.

00:01:03.010 --> 00:01:05.223 align:middle line:10%
I'm sure you hear this
all the time, right?

00:01:05.223 --> 00:01:06.640 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: I hear
it often enough.

00:01:06.640 --> 00:01:07.355 align:middle line:90%
It's very gratifying.

00:01:07.355 --> 00:01:07.680 align:middle line:90%
Sure.

00:01:07.680 --> 00:01:08.740 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:01:08.740 --> 00:01:10.840 align:middle line:84%
Did you start off--
did just tell us

00:01:10.840 --> 00:01:12.220 align:middle line:90%
a little bit about the story.

00:01:12.220 --> 00:01:15.160 align:middle line:84%
Were you really looking
for purpose in your life?

00:01:15.160 --> 00:01:17.710 align:middle line:10%
>>MILLMAN: Yes, but in
the same way everybody is.

00:01:17.710 --> 00:01:20.288 align:middle line:10%
I think we're
hard-wired goal seekers.

00:01:20.288 --> 00:01:22.330 align:middle line:10%
I watched my grandchildren
when they were little,

00:01:22.330 --> 00:01:23.560 align:middle line:10%
crawling across the floor.

00:01:23.560 --> 00:01:25.240 align:middle line:90%
They wanted something.

00:01:25.240 --> 00:01:31.180 align:middle line:84%
So like anybody, I was trying
to find out how I fit here

00:01:31.180 --> 00:01:33.070 align:middle line:84%
and what I could
do with my life.

00:01:33.070 --> 00:01:36.430 align:middle line:84%
And so that started me
contemplating and wondering,

00:01:36.430 --> 00:01:38.500 align:middle line:84%
looking at life
through that lens.

00:01:38.500 --> 00:01:39.730 align:middle line:90%
What is my purpose here?

00:01:39.730 --> 00:01:43.870 align:middle line:84%
And that developed into
much of what I've written.

00:01:43.870 --> 00:01:46.000 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So it was preceded,
though, by an accident.

00:01:46.000 --> 00:01:48.520 align:middle line:90%
We have this change in life.

00:01:48.520 --> 00:01:50.450 align:middle line:84%
There's something that
interrupts our life.

00:01:50.450 --> 00:01:51.250 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLMAN: Yes.

00:01:51.250 --> 00:01:55.210 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And we see it as
a catastrophe at the time.

00:01:55.210 --> 00:01:57.160 align:middle line:90%
And you were seeking, right?

00:01:57.160 --> 00:01:59.650 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: Well, we hear
the word disruption a lot

00:01:59.650 --> 00:02:02.110 align:middle line:84%
in business, and
politics, and technology.

00:02:02.110 --> 00:02:05.800 align:middle line:10%
And so when I shattered my
right leg in a motorcycle crash

00:02:05.800 --> 00:02:07.960 align:middle line:10%
at the peak of my career,
I was heading for the--

00:02:07.960 --> 00:02:09.250 align:middle line:10%
toward the Olympics.

00:02:09.250 --> 00:02:10.539 align:middle line:10%
It did disrupt my life.

00:02:10.539 --> 00:02:13.900 align:middle line:84%
And I began to ask
bigger questions then.

00:02:13.900 --> 00:02:16.660 align:middle line:84%
I became more
interested in, what's

00:02:16.660 --> 00:02:18.260 align:middle line:90%
the bigger picture of life?

00:02:18.260 --> 00:02:20.770 align:middle line:84%
So that's when I shifted
from being a young athlete

00:02:20.770 --> 00:02:24.145 align:middle line:84%
and coach looking for how we
create more talent for sports

00:02:24.145 --> 00:02:28.480 align:middle line:84%
to, how can we create more
talent or skill sets for life?

00:02:28.480 --> 00:02:30.400 align:middle line:90%
So daily life became the arena.

00:02:30.400 --> 00:02:32.950 align:middle line:84%
And that question sent
me around the world,

00:02:32.950 --> 00:02:34.780 align:middle line:84%
working with various
mentors, including

00:02:34.780 --> 00:02:37.680 align:middle line:90%
the old man I called Socrates.

00:02:37.680 --> 00:02:39.130 align:middle line:84%
And it developed
into an approach

00:02:39.130 --> 00:02:41.600 align:middle line:90%
to living over several decades.

00:02:41.600 --> 00:02:43.600 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Were you ever
told, though, you're never

00:02:43.600 --> 00:02:46.960 align:middle line:84%
going to walk again or perform
again the way that you were?

00:02:46.960 --> 00:02:49.870 align:middle line:84%
I mean, you've got the
naysayers on top of you,

00:02:49.870 --> 00:02:53.620 align:middle line:84%
trying to find the purpose
with the catastrophic event.

00:02:53.620 --> 00:02:56.050 align:middle line:90%
This is a perfect storm, always.

00:02:56.050 --> 00:02:57.880 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLMAN: Sure, sure.

00:02:57.880 --> 00:03:00.760 align:middle line:84%
Well, sometimes the biggest
naysayers are internal.

00:03:00.760 --> 00:03:02.100 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Isn't that the truth?

00:03:02.100 --> 00:03:03.850 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: Nick Nolte
in the movie version

00:03:03.850 --> 00:03:06.700 align:middle line:84%
said, I call myself
a peaceful warrior,

00:03:06.700 --> 00:03:08.750 align:middle line:84%
because the real battles
are inside of us.

00:03:08.750 --> 00:03:12.190 align:middle line:84%
And if we can overcome our
battles with self-doubt,

00:03:12.190 --> 00:03:15.490 align:middle line:84%
insecurity, fear, and so
on, then the challenges

00:03:15.490 --> 00:03:17.050 align:middle line:90%
of everyday life become less.

00:03:17.050 --> 00:03:19.190 align:middle line:84%
We're able to
tackle them better.

00:03:19.190 --> 00:03:21.610 align:middle line:84%
So that's what I mean
by the term warrior.

00:03:21.610 --> 00:03:24.760 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Sometimes, though, those
naysayers are what we focus on,

00:03:24.760 --> 00:03:24.920 align:middle line:90%
though.

00:03:24.920 --> 00:03:26.500 align:middle line:84%
We focus on that
person saying, well,

00:03:26.500 --> 00:03:28.550 align:middle line:84%
you never perform
the way you used to.

00:03:28.550 --> 00:03:30.240 align:middle line:90%
Did you get that line?

00:03:30.240 --> 00:03:32.440 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: Well, expectations,
including my own--

00:03:32.440 --> 00:03:33.670 align:middle line:90%
I didn't really have any.

00:03:33.670 --> 00:03:35.510 align:middle line:84%
I just said let's
see what happens.

00:03:35.510 --> 00:03:39.280 align:middle line:84%
But I began doing push-ups
before I left the hospital.

00:03:39.280 --> 00:03:40.460 align:middle line:90%
Even with a shattered leg--

00:03:40.460 --> 00:03:41.260 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:03:41.260 --> 00:03:42.843 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: --they
did a major surgery.

00:03:42.843 --> 00:03:46.690 align:middle line:84%
And I just went to the beach
and started doing strength

00:03:46.690 --> 00:03:48.520 align:middle line:90%
and said let's see what happens.

00:03:48.520 --> 00:03:51.130 align:middle line:84%
So I think this
let's see approach.

00:03:51.130 --> 00:03:53.690 align:middle line:90%
Doing my best was really a key.

00:03:53.690 --> 00:03:56.510 align:middle line:84%
That's why I never recommend to
people they strive for success.

00:03:56.510 --> 00:03:59.065 align:middle line:90%
That's not in our control.

00:03:59.065 --> 00:04:03.070 align:middle line:84%
In fact, we can control our
efforts, but not the outcomes.

00:04:03.070 --> 00:04:05.410 align:middle line:84%
But by making a good
effort over time,

00:04:05.410 --> 00:04:07.780 align:middle line:84%
we increase the odds of
getting the desired result.

00:04:07.780 --> 00:04:09.640 align:middle line:90%
So that was the approach I took.

00:04:09.640 --> 00:04:12.320 align:middle line:84%
That's why I recommend
people strive for excellence,

00:04:12.320 --> 00:04:13.427 align:middle line:90%
which is what I did.

00:04:13.427 --> 00:04:14.260 align:middle line:90%
And I kept striving.

00:04:14.260 --> 00:04:17.950 align:middle line:84%
And the story is a
comeback story, of course.

00:04:17.950 --> 00:04:19.450 align:middle line:84%
And it was successful
in its way.

00:04:19.450 --> 00:04:23.130 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: You strove for
excellence, but not perfection.

00:04:23.130 --> 00:04:24.130 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:04:24.130 --> 00:04:27.030 align:middle line:84%
My husband is a major
athlete, a state champion.

00:04:27.030 --> 00:04:29.020 align:middle line:90%
He just broke his ankle.

00:04:29.020 --> 00:04:33.970 align:middle line:84%
And he's going through
this lack of identity,

00:04:33.970 --> 00:04:36.400 align:middle line:84%
because he was so
identified there.

00:04:36.400 --> 00:04:37.940 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: I
emphasize to people,

00:04:37.940 --> 00:04:40.803 align:middle line:84%
don't say I am a
musician, I am an athlete.

00:04:40.803 --> 00:04:42.220 align:middle line:84%
Because that becomes
our identity.

00:04:42.220 --> 00:04:42.570 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:04:42.570 --> 00:04:45.195 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: And if we lose that--
and everyone does eventually--

00:04:45.195 --> 00:04:46.420 align:middle line:90%
then we say, who am I?

00:04:46.420 --> 00:04:50.890 align:middle line:84%
But if we say, I do music,
I do sports, I do medicine,

00:04:50.890 --> 00:04:53.420 align:middle line:90%
then that's not who we are.

00:04:53.420 --> 00:04:54.640 align:middle line:90%
It's just something we do.

00:04:54.640 --> 00:04:58.390 align:middle line:84%
And we do it as best we can, so
people don't have that identity

00:04:58.390 --> 00:04:59.650 align:middle line:90%
crisis as much.

00:04:59.650 --> 00:05:02.350 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Yeah, it's definitely--
because an athlete really

00:05:02.350 --> 00:05:03.600 align:middle line:90%
is all consuming.

00:05:03.600 --> 00:05:04.570 align:middle line:90%
You're physical.

00:05:04.570 --> 00:05:05.635 align:middle line:90%
It's mentally straining.

00:05:05.635 --> 00:05:06.510 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLMAN: Emotional.

00:05:06.510 --> 00:05:07.490 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Emotional.

00:05:07.490 --> 00:05:08.290 align:middle line:90%
And you have goals.

00:05:08.290 --> 00:05:11.700 align:middle line:84%
And it really is an
all-involving thing.

00:05:11.700 --> 00:05:13.740 align:middle line:90%
And it also lifted him so much.

00:05:13.740 --> 00:05:16.690 align:middle line:84%
So to be grounded is
tough, and I understand.

00:05:16.690 --> 00:05:20.730 align:middle line:84%
So at this point in your
life, what do you do?

00:05:20.730 --> 00:05:23.790 align:middle line:90%
What is your purpose now?

00:05:23.790 --> 00:05:26.490 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: Well, my purpose
now is sharing with you

00:05:26.490 --> 00:05:29.040 align:middle line:84%
and enjoying our
conversation, which I am.

00:05:29.040 --> 00:05:32.220 align:middle line:84%
So I tend to focus more on
the purpose in the moment.

00:05:32.220 --> 00:05:34.320 align:middle line:84%
Now, if someone says,
what's your cosmic purpose?

00:05:34.320 --> 00:05:36.240 align:middle line:84%
That's sometimes
tough to get your--

00:05:36.240 --> 00:05:37.593 align:middle line:90%
a grip on.

00:05:37.593 --> 00:05:39.510 align:middle line:84%
But if someone says,
what is your purpose now?

00:05:39.510 --> 00:05:42.010 align:middle line:84%
Most people know what their
purpose is in that moment.

00:05:42.010 --> 00:05:42.810 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:05:42.810 --> 00:05:43.050 align:middle line:90%
This moment.

00:05:43.050 --> 00:05:45.550 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: In my little book,
"The Four Purposes of Life,"

00:05:45.550 --> 00:05:47.080 align:middle line:90%
that's the fourth purpose.

00:05:47.080 --> 00:05:49.200 align:middle line:84%
And it may be the most
important for all of us.

00:05:49.200 --> 00:05:51.510 align:middle line:90%
What is my purpose here and now?

00:05:51.510 --> 00:05:53.760 align:middle line:84%
And that we can--
we usually know.

00:05:53.760 --> 00:05:55.590 align:middle line:90%
And we can focus on that.

00:05:55.590 --> 00:05:58.080 align:middle line:84%
And it creates more
quality moments.

00:05:58.080 --> 00:06:00.280 align:middle line:84%
And the quality of our
moments, of course,

00:06:00.280 --> 00:06:01.835 align:middle line:90%
become the quality of our life.

00:06:01.835 --> 00:06:04.290 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Now, this book, "Way
of the Peaceful Warrior"

00:06:04.290 --> 00:06:05.890 align:middle line:90%
started this.

00:06:05.890 --> 00:06:09.630 align:middle line:84%
Did you ever plan it being
an international success

00:06:09.630 --> 00:06:10.560 align:middle line:90%
when you wrote it?

00:06:10.560 --> 00:06:12.840 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: Well, my life
is much more closely

00:06:12.840 --> 00:06:16.485 align:middle line:84%
resembling improvisational
comedy to strategic planning.

00:06:16.485 --> 00:06:17.770 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:06:17.770 --> 00:06:19.140 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: A combination of both?

00:06:19.140 --> 00:06:20.610 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: I just
shared something

00:06:20.610 --> 00:06:25.405 align:middle line:84%
that was meaningful to me, based
on my previous life experience.

00:06:25.405 --> 00:06:27.780 align:middle line:84%
And I thought maybe a few
college students would like it.

00:06:27.780 --> 00:06:30.720 align:middle line:84%
I really couldn't have
predicted the impact

00:06:30.720 --> 00:06:34.360 align:middle line:84%
it had over the decades,
really, and continues to have.

00:06:34.360 --> 00:06:35.700 align:middle line:90%
I say that without hubris.

00:06:35.700 --> 00:06:38.400 align:middle line:84%
It just still
surprises me, but there

00:06:38.400 --> 00:06:41.040 align:middle line:84%
must have been something
that caught lightning.

00:06:41.040 --> 00:06:43.800 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It really was one
of the first books that

00:06:43.800 --> 00:06:47.850 align:middle line:84%
described the hero's journey
in a metaphorical way.

00:06:47.850 --> 00:06:50.550 align:middle line:84%
It happened to have been the
autobiography of your life,

00:06:50.550 --> 00:06:52.853 align:middle line:84%
but done in such
a wonderful way.

00:06:52.853 --> 00:06:54.270 align:middle line:84%
I mean, have you
heard from people

00:06:54.270 --> 00:06:57.340 align:middle line:84%
over the years, why it made
such a big impact 25 years ago?

00:06:57.340 --> 00:06:58.140 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLMAN: Yes.

00:06:58.140 --> 00:07:00.240 align:middle line:84%
I asked people, because
they would repeat

00:07:00.240 --> 00:07:01.907 align:middle line:84%
the same thing over
and over-- this book

00:07:01.907 --> 00:07:03.090 align:middle line:90%
changed my life in some way.

00:07:03.090 --> 00:07:04.260 align:middle line:90%
And I wanted to say, why?

00:07:04.260 --> 00:07:05.160 align:middle line:90%
How?

00:07:05.160 --> 00:07:08.010 align:middle line:84%
And I think what it did was
it helped expand perspectives

00:07:08.010 --> 00:07:10.800 align:middle line:84%
about our promise
and possibilities.

00:07:10.800 --> 00:07:13.710 align:middle line:84%
I think it offered reminders
that people tend to know

00:07:13.710 --> 00:07:16.270 align:middle line:90%
deep down, but we forget.

00:07:16.270 --> 00:07:17.470 align:middle line:90%
So that's what I do today.

00:07:17.470 --> 00:07:21.040 align:middle line:84%
I offer reminders and
perspectives with people.

00:07:21.040 --> 00:07:23.420 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Now, you speak to
corporations and everyone.

00:07:23.420 --> 00:07:25.150 align:middle line:84%
And this theme is
around purpose?

00:07:25.150 --> 00:07:27.105 align:middle line:84%
Is that what you
speak about now?

00:07:27.105 --> 00:07:30.262 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: Well, that's one of
the major themes in my work.

00:07:30.262 --> 00:07:32.220 align:middle line:84%
People say, what do you
mean, peaceful warrior?

00:07:32.220 --> 00:07:33.340 align:middle line:90%
What is that about?

00:07:33.340 --> 00:07:34.980 align:middle line:90%
And it's really about all of us.

00:07:34.980 --> 00:07:37.200 align:middle line:84%
This is not so much
about me as us.

00:07:37.200 --> 00:07:39.733 align:middle line:90%
We're all in this together.

00:07:39.733 --> 00:07:41.400 align:middle line:84%
It's about living
with a peaceful heart.

00:07:41.400 --> 00:07:43.240 align:middle line:90%
We're all striving to do that.

00:07:43.240 --> 00:07:45.420 align:middle line:84%
But it's also
recognizing the times

00:07:45.420 --> 00:07:48.840 align:middle line:84%
we need a warrior spirit to
really face what we need to

00:07:48.840 --> 00:07:52.140 align:middle line:90%
in the arena of daily life.

00:07:52.140 --> 00:07:55.770 align:middle line:84%
So that's really what
I wanted to share.

00:07:55.770 --> 00:07:57.560 align:middle line:90%
And it's an approach to living.

00:07:57.560 --> 00:08:00.150 align:middle line:84%
It includes life skills
like learning to live

00:08:00.150 --> 00:08:01.830 align:middle line:90%
in the present moment and why.

00:08:01.830 --> 00:08:04.060 align:middle line:90%
What does that really mean?

00:08:04.060 --> 00:08:06.330 align:middle line:84%
And also, living
a purposeful life.

00:08:06.330 --> 00:08:10.110 align:middle line:84%
And several of my books deal
with that central question of,

00:08:10.110 --> 00:08:11.070 align:middle line:90%
what are we here to do?

00:08:11.070 --> 00:08:12.120 align:middle line:90%
And what are we doing here?

00:08:12.120 --> 00:08:12.660 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:08:12.660 --> 00:08:13.050 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:08:13.050 --> 00:08:14.880 align:middle line:84%
As I mentioned, that's one
of the biggest questions

00:08:14.880 --> 00:08:15.680 align:middle line:90%
from callers.

00:08:15.680 --> 00:08:18.120 align:middle line:84%
So how do you get
to that answer?

00:08:18.120 --> 00:08:21.450 align:middle line:90%
What is purpose?

00:08:21.450 --> 00:08:23.160 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: Well,
that was something

00:08:23.160 --> 00:08:25.470 align:middle line:90%
that was unfocused in my life.

00:08:25.470 --> 00:08:27.240 align:middle line:90%
And I met various mentors.

00:08:27.240 --> 00:08:29.610 align:middle line:84%
I didn't write another book
after "Way of the Peaceful

00:08:29.610 --> 00:08:31.050 align:middle line:90%
Warrior" for 10 years.

00:08:31.050 --> 00:08:33.030 align:middle line:84%
I felt I'd said
what I had to say.

00:08:33.030 --> 00:08:35.400 align:middle line:84%
Then other mentors
entered my life.

00:08:35.400 --> 00:08:36.450 align:middle line:90%
And I was so excited--

00:08:36.450 --> 00:08:39.390 align:middle line:84%
this radically new
cutting-edge information.

00:08:39.390 --> 00:08:42.120 align:middle line:84%
So that stimulated "Sacred
Journey of the Peaceful

00:08:42.120 --> 00:08:45.180 align:middle line:84%
Warrior," the second book I
wrote 10 years later, and then

00:08:45.180 --> 00:08:47.480 align:middle line:84%
"No Ordinary Moments," and
a number of other books--

00:08:47.480 --> 00:08:49.320 align:middle line:90%
17 that eventually followed.

00:08:49.320 --> 00:08:52.210 align:middle line:84%
I've never written a book just
to have another book out there.

00:08:52.210 --> 00:08:53.350 align:middle line:90%
It has to justify itself.

00:08:53.350 --> 00:08:54.150 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:08:54.150 --> 00:08:57.930 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: So there are
many facets of this way.

00:08:57.930 --> 00:08:59.100 align:middle line:90%
One of my mentors--

00:08:59.100 --> 00:09:00.990 align:middle line:90%
I call him the warrior priest--

00:09:00.990 --> 00:09:05.550 align:middle line:84%
had an uncannily accurate system
for deriving one's life path--

00:09:05.550 --> 00:09:08.130 align:middle line:90%


00:09:08.130 --> 00:09:11.820 align:middle line:84%
clarifying, crystallizing,
illuminating the core

00:09:11.820 --> 00:09:15.430 align:middle line:84%
issues of our life, and some
hurdles we're here to overcome,

00:09:15.430 --> 00:09:17.130 align:middle line:90%
and the strengths we have.

00:09:17.130 --> 00:09:20.260 align:middle line:84%
And he gave a series of
lectures, and I attended.

00:09:20.260 --> 00:09:23.070 align:middle line:84%
And I began to teach
friends, relatives anything,

00:09:23.070 --> 00:09:25.840 align:middle line:84%
doing readings for them,
kind of consultations.

00:09:25.840 --> 00:09:27.270 align:middle line:90%
And over the years, I finally--

00:09:27.270 --> 00:09:29.610 align:middle line:84%
after eight years,
I decided it was

00:09:29.610 --> 00:09:31.530 align:middle line:84%
time to write a book
with the material.

00:09:31.530 --> 00:09:33.570 align:middle line:10%
And that became a
book called "The Life

00:09:33.570 --> 00:09:34.682 align:middle line:10%
You Were Born to Live."

00:09:34.682 --> 00:09:35.890 align:middle line:10%
>>LISA: Which is really cool.

00:09:35.890 --> 00:09:37.680 align:middle line:10%
So that gets you
to life purpose--

00:09:37.680 --> 00:09:38.550 align:middle line:10%
>>MILLMAN: Yes.

00:09:38.550 --> 00:09:40.380 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: --through a
series of calculations

00:09:40.380 --> 00:09:42.340 align:middle line:84%
using your birth
date and so forth.

00:09:42.340 --> 00:09:44.340 align:middle line:10%
And there's a whole
Life Purpose Calculator

00:09:44.340 --> 00:09:46.103 align:middle line:10%
on your website, which I love.

00:09:46.103 --> 00:09:48.270 align:middle line:10%
It's the Way of the Peaceful
Warrior website, right?

00:09:48.270 --> 00:09:49.672 align:middle line:10%
>>MILLMAN: Yes.

00:09:49.672 --> 00:09:51.880 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And then you can
calculate your life purpose.

00:09:51.880 --> 00:09:55.260 align:middle line:84%
And has it really proved to
be accurate for people that

00:09:55.260 --> 00:09:56.958 align:middle line:90%
go on there and check it out?

00:09:56.958 --> 00:09:58.500 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: Well, of
course, no author

00:09:58.500 --> 00:10:00.290 align:middle line:90%
is going to say, no, not really.

00:10:00.290 --> 00:10:05.820 align:middle line:84%
But, yes, it has some
uncanny accuracy.

00:10:05.820 --> 00:10:09.750 align:middle line:84%
I don't understand it, how
deriving from your birth date--

00:10:09.750 --> 00:10:12.450 align:middle line:84%
I mean, astrologers do things
with that, and the time

00:10:12.450 --> 00:10:13.590 align:middle line:90%
of your birth, and so on.

00:10:13.590 --> 00:10:15.510 align:middle line:90%
This is very accessible.

00:10:15.510 --> 00:10:19.400 align:middle line:84%
I've studied all the systems of
self-analysis, self-knowledge.

00:10:19.400 --> 00:10:21.540 align:middle line:90%
Very important.

00:10:21.540 --> 00:10:23.000 align:middle line:90%
The Oracle at Delphi--

00:10:23.000 --> 00:10:25.610 align:middle line:84%
over the gates, they
had "Know thyself."

00:10:25.610 --> 00:10:26.870 align:middle line:90%
It's ancient wisdom.

00:10:26.870 --> 00:10:29.120 align:middle line:84%
And every religious
and spiritual tradition

00:10:29.120 --> 00:10:30.620 align:middle line:90%
says know yourself.

00:10:30.620 --> 00:10:32.450 align:middle line:84%
Because if we don't
know ourself--

00:10:32.450 --> 00:10:35.300 align:middle line:84%
if we're looking at a kind
of illusion we've developed,

00:10:35.300 --> 00:10:38.630 align:middle line:84%
then we make the right
decisions for the wrong person,

00:10:38.630 --> 00:10:40.580 align:middle line:90%
the one we thought we were.

00:10:40.580 --> 00:10:42.410 align:middle line:84%
So "The Life You
Were Born to Live"

00:10:42.410 --> 00:10:45.920 align:middle line:84%
is to help people really
know themselves to the bone

00:10:45.920 --> 00:10:48.350 align:middle line:84%
and make wiser decisions
for who they truly

00:10:48.350 --> 00:10:51.500 align:middle line:84%
are and have more
compassion for themselves

00:10:51.500 --> 00:10:53.060 align:middle line:90%
and others in their lives.

00:10:53.060 --> 00:10:56.510 align:middle line:84%
Because you can also look
up loved ones, friends,

00:10:56.510 --> 00:11:00.390 align:middle line:84%
and understand the path they're
taking up that mountain.

00:11:00.390 --> 00:11:04.580 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So would you consider
yourself an introvert?

00:11:04.580 --> 00:11:07.470 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: I'd have
to say it varies.

00:11:07.470 --> 00:11:09.960 align:middle line:84%
There are times I go into very
introverted, introspective

00:11:09.960 --> 00:11:12.570 align:middle line:90%
times, working on new books.

00:11:12.570 --> 00:11:15.480 align:middle line:84%
And I need time to
recharge on my own.

00:11:15.480 --> 00:11:18.090 align:middle line:84%
But other times, I'm very
gregarious and outgoing,

00:11:18.090 --> 00:11:20.072 align:middle line:84%
so I think there's
a mixture there.

00:11:20.072 --> 00:11:21.780 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So you take
this personality type

00:11:21.780 --> 00:11:25.000 align:middle line:84%
that you just explained about
yourself and the introvert

00:11:25.000 --> 00:11:26.910 align:middle line:90%
and at times being gregarious.

00:11:26.910 --> 00:11:30.130 align:middle line:84%
And you fit that into,
how do I show up?

00:11:30.130 --> 00:11:31.750 align:middle line:90%
How do I show up in life?

00:11:31.750 --> 00:11:33.460 align:middle line:84%
What do I do with
these personalities?

00:11:33.460 --> 00:11:36.600 align:middle line:84%
How do I achieve
anything in my life?

00:11:36.600 --> 00:11:39.187 align:middle line:84%
It becomes confusing,
doesn't it?

00:11:39.187 --> 00:11:41.270 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: Well, it certainly
can, especially when

00:11:41.270 --> 00:11:43.300 align:middle line:90%
we project into the future.

00:11:43.300 --> 00:11:46.770 align:middle line:84%
But if we say, how do I
show up right now and strive

00:11:46.770 --> 00:11:48.900 align:middle line:90%
to be as authentic as we can?

00:11:48.900 --> 00:11:51.180 align:middle line:84%
Like what you see
is what you get.

00:11:51.180 --> 00:11:52.980 align:middle line:84%
I'm not different
with other people

00:11:52.980 --> 00:11:54.820 align:middle line:90%
or in other circumstances.

00:11:54.820 --> 00:11:57.030 align:middle line:84%
So I have developed
a sense of who I am.

00:11:57.030 --> 00:11:59.440 align:middle line:84%
Authenticity has always
been very important to me.

00:11:59.440 --> 00:12:00.570 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah, you can tell.

00:12:00.570 --> 00:12:01.320 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:12:01.320 --> 00:12:02.490 align:middle line:90%
And the way that you write--

00:12:02.490 --> 00:12:04.032 align:middle line:84%
I love that you say
you write a book,

00:12:04.032 --> 00:12:06.810 align:middle line:84%
because it's got to have
a meaning in your life.

00:12:06.810 --> 00:12:08.530 align:middle line:84%
It's got to come
from an experience.

00:12:08.530 --> 00:12:09.330 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLMAN: Yes.

00:12:09.330 --> 00:12:11.860 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And you take your time
to do something like that.

00:12:11.860 --> 00:12:13.630 align:middle line:84%
And it really gets
to the next place.

00:12:13.630 --> 00:12:15.870 align:middle line:84%
So at what point did "Way
of the Peaceful Warrior"

00:12:15.870 --> 00:12:17.190 align:middle line:90%
get adapted to a film?

00:12:17.190 --> 00:12:19.410 align:middle line:90%
Tell us that story.

00:12:19.410 --> 00:12:21.270 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: Well,
first I got called

00:12:21.270 --> 00:12:24.250 align:middle line:84%
from Robert Downey, Jr. He
said, you want to have dinner?

00:12:24.250 --> 00:12:26.605 align:middle line:84%
I'm in San Francisco,
and we're making a film.

00:12:26.605 --> 00:12:28.230 align:middle line:84%
He was just starting
out in his career.

00:12:28.230 --> 00:12:30.810 align:middle line:84%
He said, I'd like to play
your role in the movie.

00:12:30.810 --> 00:12:33.330 align:middle line:90%
And I flew to Columbia.

00:12:33.330 --> 00:12:36.000 align:middle line:84%
And oddly enough, there's a
longer story I won't go into,

00:12:36.000 --> 00:12:38.280 align:middle line:90%
but I said no.

00:12:38.280 --> 00:12:41.370 align:middle line:84%
I know it sounds a little
crazy right now in retrospect.

00:12:41.370 --> 00:12:45.190 align:middle line:84%
Then somebody-- another
company offered to do the film.

00:12:45.190 --> 00:12:47.220 align:middle line:90%
And I said I declined.

00:12:47.220 --> 00:12:49.920 align:middle line:84%
And then there was this
really good-hearted guy

00:12:49.920 --> 00:12:53.460 align:middle line:84%
who was an aspiring producer who
said, I'd like to do your film.

00:12:53.460 --> 00:12:55.770 align:middle line:84%
And for various
reasons, I said yes.

00:12:55.770 --> 00:12:59.160 align:middle line:84%
And it only took him 18 years
to finally have a company.

00:12:59.160 --> 00:13:01.360 align:middle line:90%
Sobini Films produced the film.

00:13:01.360 --> 00:13:04.350 align:middle line:84%
And it was distributed by
Lionsgate, then Universal.

00:13:04.350 --> 00:13:06.010 align:middle line:90%
So, yeah.

00:13:06.010 --> 00:13:10.560 align:middle line:84%
It took-- from the time the
book was first published,

00:13:10.560 --> 00:13:15.720 align:middle line:84%
well over 20 years
to create the film.

00:13:15.720 --> 00:13:17.800 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Was it important
for you to create it?

00:13:17.800 --> 00:13:20.400 align:middle line:90%
Or you wanted it done right?

00:13:20.400 --> 00:13:23.010 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: Well, I don't
know what done right is.

00:13:23.010 --> 00:13:25.990 align:middle line:84%
A movie is a meal for
consciousness in two hours.

00:13:25.990 --> 00:13:27.900 align:middle line:84%
So movies can rarely
capture what's

00:13:27.900 --> 00:13:30.750 align:middle line:84%
in the book of the internal
life of the character

00:13:30.750 --> 00:13:34.110 align:middle line:84%
and yet, I was honored that they
were willing to spend the money

00:13:34.110 --> 00:13:36.120 align:middle line:90%
to adapt my work to film.

00:13:36.120 --> 00:13:38.337 align:middle line:90%
And it was an exciting time.

00:13:38.337 --> 00:13:40.920 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Were you a part of the
process in choosing Nick Nolte?

00:13:40.920 --> 00:13:41.720 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLMAN: No, no.

00:13:41.720 --> 00:13:42.990 align:middle line:90%
I sold the rights.

00:13:42.990 --> 00:13:45.560 align:middle line:84%
And I was a
cheerleader-- that's it--

00:13:45.560 --> 00:13:47.160 align:middle line:84%
to the project,
wishing them well

00:13:47.160 --> 00:13:49.410 align:middle line:84%
and letting the
professionals do their thing.

00:13:49.410 --> 00:13:51.760 align:middle line:84%
I did contribute some
scenes at the last minute--

00:13:51.760 --> 00:13:53.730 align:middle line:84%
a couple of lines
in some scenes.

00:13:53.730 --> 00:13:55.990 align:middle line:90%
But I wasn't the screenwriter.

00:13:55.990 --> 00:13:57.730 align:middle line:84%
I was just supportive
of the project.

00:13:57.730 --> 00:14:00.390 align:middle line:84%
And I think it reaches a
new and different audience.

00:14:00.390 --> 00:14:01.950 align:middle line:90%
It's become sort of a cult film.

00:14:01.950 --> 00:14:02.490 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:14:02.490 --> 00:14:03.000 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, it's great.

00:14:03.000 --> 00:14:04.080 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: And many
people then read the book,

00:14:04.080 --> 00:14:05.060 align:middle line:90%
which is all to the good.

00:14:05.060 --> 00:14:05.520 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:14:05.520 --> 00:14:07.530 align:middle line:84%
Let's actually take
a look of the trailer

00:14:07.530 --> 00:14:10.320 align:middle line:84%
of the movie, the way of
the "Peaceful Warrior."

00:14:10.320 --> 00:14:15.060 align:middle line:84%
>> I call myself a
peaceful warrior,

00:14:15.060 --> 00:14:17.720 align:middle line:84%
because the battles we
fight are on the inside.

00:14:17.720 --> 00:14:20.880 align:middle line:90%


00:14:20.880 --> 00:14:23.325 align:middle line:84%
This moment is the only
thing that matters.

00:14:23.325 --> 00:14:29.968 align:middle line:90%


00:14:29.968 --> 00:14:30.768 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Socrates.

00:14:30.768 --> 00:14:31.350 align:middle line:90%
Socrates.

00:14:31.350 --> 00:14:32.280 align:middle line:90%
Who?

00:14:32.280 --> 00:14:34.980 align:middle line:90%
How did you find the Socrates?

00:14:34.980 --> 00:14:38.673 align:middle line:84%
Did you just have to
be a seeker, really?

00:14:38.673 --> 00:14:39.840 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLMAN: There's a saying.

00:14:39.840 --> 00:14:42.280 align:middle line:84%
Many people have heard that
when the student is ready,

00:14:42.280 --> 00:14:43.320 align:middle line:90%
the teacher appears.

00:14:43.320 --> 00:14:45.810 align:middle line:84%
And many people
imagine that to mean

00:14:45.810 --> 00:14:47.990 align:middle line:84%
when I'm deserving enough
or prepared enough,

00:14:47.990 --> 00:14:50.400 align:middle line:84%
a teacher will appear
like Socrates in my life

00:14:50.400 --> 00:14:52.020 align:middle line:90%
and guide me up the path.

00:14:52.020 --> 00:14:54.180 align:middle line:84%
But I believe what it
means-- when the student is

00:14:54.180 --> 00:14:57.000 align:middle line:84%
ready or actually
paying attention,

00:14:57.000 --> 00:14:59.310 align:middle line:90%
the teacher appears everywhere.

00:14:59.310 --> 00:15:01.990 align:middle line:84%
So Socrates-- for me,
I was coming off--

00:15:01.990 --> 00:15:04.200 align:middle line:84%
I read the Carlos
Castaneda books.

00:15:04.200 --> 00:15:08.010 align:middle line:84%
But I wanted to show that you
could find a teacher anywhere.

00:15:08.010 --> 00:15:10.310 align:middle line:84%
And I remembered
a cosmic fellow I

00:15:10.310 --> 00:15:12.430 align:middle line:84%
had met who wouldn't
tell me his real name,

00:15:12.430 --> 00:15:14.700 align:middle line:84%
but he reminded me
of the Greek sage,

00:15:14.700 --> 00:15:17.160 align:middle line:84%
so I started calling
him Socrates.

00:15:17.160 --> 00:15:21.360 align:middle line:84%
And he represented the
archetypal teacher.

00:15:21.360 --> 00:15:24.090 align:middle line:84%
Frodo had Gandalf in
"Lord of the Rings,"

00:15:24.090 --> 00:15:27.790 align:middle line:90%
and Arthur had Merlin.

00:15:27.790 --> 00:15:30.930 align:middle line:84%
Danielson had Mr. Miyagi
in the "Karate Kid."

00:15:30.930 --> 00:15:33.420 align:middle line:84%
So this archetypal
student-teacher relationship

00:15:33.420 --> 00:15:35.280 align:middle line:90%
is one way to convey ideas.

00:15:35.280 --> 00:15:36.750 align:middle line:90%
And it was all intuitive.

00:15:36.750 --> 00:15:39.000 align:middle line:84%
But I said, I think
I'll share these lessons

00:15:39.000 --> 00:15:40.650 align:middle line:90%
I learned over the years.

00:15:40.650 --> 00:15:43.080 align:middle line:84%
Because I wrote the book 14
years after I met Socrates.

00:15:43.080 --> 00:15:44.400 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh.

00:15:44.400 --> 00:15:46.650 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: So it was
all my life experience.

00:15:46.650 --> 00:15:49.920 align:middle line:84%
Maybe my own higher self
as well contributed somehow

00:15:49.920 --> 00:15:53.130 align:middle line:90%
to what went down in the book.

00:15:53.130 --> 00:15:55.467 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Have you always
wanted to be an author?

00:15:55.467 --> 00:15:56.550 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLMAN: Oh, not at all.

00:15:56.550 --> 00:15:57.190 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Not at all, huh?

00:15:57.190 --> 00:15:57.990 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLMAN: Yeah.

00:15:57.990 --> 00:16:00.167 align:middle line:84%
A 10-page paper in
college was intimidating.

00:16:00.167 --> 00:16:02.250 align:middle line:84%
Like most of us, how am I
going to write 10 pages?

00:16:02.250 --> 00:16:02.750 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:16:02.750 --> 00:16:04.620 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: But it happened
over a process with time.

00:16:04.620 --> 00:16:05.662 align:middle line:90%
I've always seen myself--

00:16:05.662 --> 00:16:08.490 align:middle line:84%
I love to teach, so I taught
gymnastics-- what I knew.

00:16:08.490 --> 00:16:11.860 align:middle line:84%
But later it segued over
to something bigger.

00:16:11.860 --> 00:16:14.680 align:middle line:84%
When my interests
expanded into daily life,

00:16:14.680 --> 00:16:18.540 align:middle line:84%
I started looking for things
that could really help people.

00:16:18.540 --> 00:16:21.100 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: You expanded,
too, and as a coach,

00:16:21.100 --> 00:16:23.670 align:middle line:84%
which we talked a little bit
about this on my radio show,

00:16:23.670 --> 00:16:27.150 align:middle line:84%
that a coach really
is an earned title.

00:16:27.150 --> 00:16:28.288 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLMAN: Yes.

00:16:28.288 --> 00:16:30.330 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Randomly, people
call themselves coaches.

00:16:30.330 --> 00:16:33.630 align:middle line:84%
And then they have a lot of
influence over young people.

00:16:33.630 --> 00:16:37.770 align:middle line:84%
And that comes with a certain
amount of credibility,

00:16:37.770 --> 00:16:39.420 align:middle line:90%
and honor, and authenticity.

00:16:39.420 --> 00:16:41.160 align:middle line:84%
Somebody really
needs to understand

00:16:41.160 --> 00:16:42.180 align:middle line:90%
what that word means.

00:16:42.180 --> 00:16:46.320 align:middle line:84%
What does being a
coach mean to you?

00:16:46.320 --> 00:16:48.190 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: The word
supportive comes to me.

00:16:48.190 --> 00:16:51.370 align:middle line:84%
A coach is there to support
you and your process.

00:16:51.370 --> 00:16:54.510 align:middle line:84%
One of the central tenets of
"The Peaceful Warrior's Way"

00:16:54.510 --> 00:16:58.530 align:middle line:84%
is that there is no best book,
teacher, religion, path, diet,

00:16:58.530 --> 00:17:00.450 align:middle line:90%
exercise system.

00:17:00.450 --> 00:17:02.180 align:middle line:84%
There's only the
best for each of us

00:17:02.180 --> 00:17:04.109 align:middle line:90%
at a given time of our lives.

00:17:04.109 --> 00:17:05.339 align:middle line:90%
Life is an experiment.

00:17:05.339 --> 00:17:08.945 align:middle line:84%
So I have a profound respect
for each person's process.

00:17:08.945 --> 00:17:11.619 align:middle line:84%
So as a coach, I
look to that person.

00:17:11.619 --> 00:17:13.109 align:middle line:90%
I'm there to support them.

00:17:13.109 --> 00:17:14.400 align:middle line:90%
I often remind people.

00:17:14.400 --> 00:17:16.410 align:middle line:84%
I'm not here for
people to trust me.

00:17:16.410 --> 00:17:18.560 align:middle line:84%
I'm here to help people
trust themselves.

00:17:18.560 --> 00:17:21.210 align:middle line:84%
And so to me, that's
what a coach is.

00:17:21.210 --> 00:17:23.460 align:middle line:84%
And I began coaching
in gymnastics.

00:17:23.460 --> 00:17:27.839 align:middle line:84%
A coach has to address
someone's mind, emotions, body,

00:17:27.839 --> 00:17:30.690 align:middle line:84%
whereas maybe a teacher in
college-- it's more academic.

00:17:30.690 --> 00:17:32.610 align:middle line:90%
They just do the lectures.

00:17:32.610 --> 00:17:35.190 align:middle line:84%
And the student goes and
reads the books and studies.

00:17:35.190 --> 00:17:37.590 align:middle line:84%
So we have a much more
intimate and deep connection

00:17:37.590 --> 00:17:39.130 align:middle line:90%
with people.

00:17:39.130 --> 00:17:42.310 align:middle line:84%
I think a good psychotherapist
is a coach as well.

00:17:42.310 --> 00:17:44.220 align:middle line:84%
So it's more than
a word or title

00:17:44.220 --> 00:17:47.870 align:middle line:84%
someone uses like, I'm a life
coach, which is terrific.

00:17:47.870 --> 00:17:49.893 align:middle line:84%
It's great to have a
lot of people around.

00:17:49.893 --> 00:17:51.060 align:middle line:90%
And we can coach each other.

00:17:51.060 --> 00:17:51.270 align:middle line:90%
I mean--

00:17:51.270 --> 00:17:51.450 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:17:51.450 --> 00:17:53.440 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: --we're all
students and teachers.

00:17:53.440 --> 00:17:54.120 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Friends and so forth.

00:17:54.120 --> 00:17:54.930 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLMAN: Sure.

00:17:54.930 --> 00:17:57.870 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: You said to me once
that life is about the journey,

00:17:57.870 --> 00:18:00.238 align:middle line:84%
but it's also about
the destination.

00:18:00.238 --> 00:18:02.280 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: Well, in the
"Peaceful Warrior" movie,

00:18:02.280 --> 00:18:04.620 align:middle line:84%
the character Dan
has a revelation,

00:18:04.620 --> 00:18:06.990 align:middle line:84%
that it's the journey
that makes us happy,

00:18:06.990 --> 00:18:09.540 align:middle line:84%
not just reaching the
destination, which

00:18:09.540 --> 00:18:11.280 align:middle line:90%
is a wise idea.

00:18:11.280 --> 00:18:14.880 align:middle line:84%
But without a destination in
mind, there is no journey.

00:18:14.880 --> 00:18:16.470 align:middle line:90%
We just wander around.

00:18:16.470 --> 00:18:19.530 align:middle line:84%
So from our point A, we
need to pick a point B,

00:18:19.530 --> 00:18:22.620 align:middle line:84%
whether it's for the day,
for the minute, for the hour,

00:18:22.620 --> 00:18:24.450 align:middle line:90%
something we're moving toward.

00:18:24.450 --> 00:18:28.620 align:middle line:84%
To me, success is
making progress

00:18:28.620 --> 00:18:31.320 align:middle line:84%
toward a goal that's
meaningful to us.

00:18:31.320 --> 00:18:35.190 align:middle line:84%
That's really a meaningful
way to define success.

00:18:35.190 --> 00:18:36.720 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes, it is.

00:18:36.720 --> 00:18:38.977 align:middle line:90%
And if the goal changes--

00:18:38.977 --> 00:18:40.810 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: We move in
a different direction.

00:18:40.810 --> 00:18:42.550 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: But we enjoy
the journey and the way.

00:18:42.550 --> 00:18:42.870 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLMAN: Sure.

00:18:42.870 --> 00:18:43.280 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: The path.

00:18:43.280 --> 00:18:45.008 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: Most of
it's the journey.

00:18:45.008 --> 00:18:47.550 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Right-- which is always
filled with bumps, and rocks,

00:18:47.550 --> 00:18:49.835 align:middle line:90%
and routes, and obstacles.

00:18:49.835 --> 00:18:50.960 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLMAN: Yes, spiritual--

00:18:50.960 --> 00:18:51.960 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Training points.

00:18:51.960 --> 00:18:53.400 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLMAN: --weightlifting.

00:18:53.400 --> 00:18:55.530 align:middle line:84%
Many times we volunteer
for adversity,

00:18:55.530 --> 00:18:57.990 align:middle line:90%
because we intuit the value.

00:18:57.990 --> 00:18:59.220 align:middle line:90%
Sometimes I ask audiences.

00:18:59.220 --> 00:19:01.053 align:middle line:84%
Please raise your hand
if you've experienced

00:19:01.053 --> 00:19:03.550 align:middle line:84%
physical, emotional, or
mental pain in your life.

00:19:03.550 --> 00:19:05.660 align:middle line:90%
Everybody raises their hand.

00:19:05.660 --> 00:19:07.710 align:middle line:84%
And yet, because of that
pain, that challenge,

00:19:07.710 --> 00:19:09.845 align:middle line:84%
that difficulty, we're
a little bit stronger,

00:19:09.845 --> 00:19:13.260 align:middle line:84%
a little bit wiser, and maybe
even have a bigger perspective

00:19:13.260 --> 00:19:14.400 align:middle line:90%
about life.

00:19:14.400 --> 00:19:16.910 align:middle line:84%
So we don't have to
pretend to like adversity.

00:19:16.910 --> 00:19:19.860 align:middle line:84%
But when a challenge happens,
we roll up our sleeves.

00:19:19.860 --> 00:19:21.990 align:middle line:84%
And we know we're going
to get stronger and wiser

00:19:21.990 --> 00:19:22.800 align:middle line:90%
from doing it.

00:19:22.800 --> 00:19:24.100 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: If we could
just remember that--

00:19:24.100 --> 00:19:24.660 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLMAN: Yes.

00:19:24.660 --> 00:19:26.430 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: --and not go back
into those old patterns.

00:19:26.430 --> 00:19:26.910 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLMAN: Right.

00:19:26.910 --> 00:19:27.240 align:middle line:90%
Why me?

00:19:27.240 --> 00:19:27.870 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:19:27.870 --> 00:19:28.870 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLMAN: Why is this--

00:19:28.870 --> 00:19:30.930 align:middle line:84%
not the victim, but why
is it happening to me?

00:19:30.930 --> 00:19:31.730 align:middle line:90%
But, all right.

00:19:31.730 --> 00:19:33.260 align:middle line:90%
Time to roll up my sleeves.

00:19:33.260 --> 00:19:34.190 align:middle line:90%
I've done it before.

00:19:34.190 --> 00:19:35.130 align:middle line:90%
I can do it again.

00:19:35.130 --> 00:19:36.180 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: If we can remember that.

00:19:36.180 --> 00:19:37.290 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLMAN: Yes, exactly.

00:19:37.290 --> 00:19:39.178 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: The book,
"The Four Purposes--"

00:19:39.178 --> 00:19:40.220 align:middle line:90%
you mentioned the fourth.

00:19:40.220 --> 00:19:41.780 align:middle line:90%
What are the first three?

00:19:41.780 --> 00:19:44.030 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: Well, the first
purpose is something we all

00:19:44.030 --> 00:19:45.500 align:middle line:90%
share--

00:19:45.500 --> 00:19:47.037 align:middle line:90%
learning life's lessons.

00:19:47.037 --> 00:19:48.620 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And we just
talked about that.

00:19:48.620 --> 00:19:48.890 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:19:48.890 --> 00:19:49.690 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLMAN: Yeah.

00:19:49.690 --> 00:19:51.330 align:middle line:84%
And many people go,
well, I know that.

00:19:51.330 --> 00:19:52.997 align:middle line:84%
Of course, we learn
from our experience.

00:19:52.997 --> 00:19:57.380 align:middle line:84%
But it's more about the idea
that Earth is a divine school.

00:19:57.380 --> 00:19:59.780 align:middle line:90%
And daily life is our classroom.

00:19:59.780 --> 00:20:01.850 align:middle line:84%
Daily life is
guaranteed to teach us

00:20:01.850 --> 00:20:03.740 align:middle line:84%
everything we need
to learn in order

00:20:03.740 --> 00:20:04.990 align:middle line:90%
to evolve as human beings--

00:20:04.990 --> 00:20:06.198 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Guaranteed, isn't it?

00:20:06.198 --> 00:20:08.360 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: --to really
appreciate the challenges.

00:20:08.360 --> 00:20:10.850 align:middle line:84%
A man wrote to me once and
said, Dan, I read your book.

00:20:10.850 --> 00:20:12.780 align:middle line:84%
And now, I want to do
more spiritual practice,

00:20:12.780 --> 00:20:14.193 align:middle line:90%
but I'm married.

00:20:14.193 --> 00:20:15.110 align:middle line:90%
I have three children.

00:20:15.110 --> 00:20:17.090 align:middle line:90%
I'm married, full-time job.

00:20:17.090 --> 00:20:22.040 align:middle line:84%
He came to understand
his work, his family

00:20:22.040 --> 00:20:23.960 align:middle line:90%
were his spiritual practices.

00:20:23.960 --> 00:20:24.890 align:middle line:90%
And they develop us.

00:20:24.890 --> 00:20:28.340 align:middle line:84%
They demand more and develop
us more than sitting in a cave

00:20:28.340 --> 00:20:29.170 align:middle line:90%
and meditating.

00:20:29.170 --> 00:20:29.970 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Completely.

00:20:29.970 --> 00:20:32.085 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: I know
because I've done both.

00:20:32.085 --> 00:20:33.710 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Yes, that's
a great point where

00:20:33.710 --> 00:20:36.370 align:middle line:84%
you get-- leave work and then
you go do your yoga class

00:20:36.370 --> 00:20:37.900 align:middle line:84%
or you do your
spiritual practice.

00:20:37.900 --> 00:20:40.480 align:middle line:84%
Well, what if you can bring
those principles of balance--

00:20:40.480 --> 00:20:42.000 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLMAN: Yeah, everything.

00:20:42.000 --> 00:20:42.800 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:20:42.800 --> 00:20:49.220 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: --into work and of being
the observer into situations?

00:20:49.220 --> 00:20:51.290 align:middle line:84%
All those great
spiritual practices

00:20:51.290 --> 00:20:53.630 align:middle line:84%
in real daily life, I
think, is the real school--

00:20:53.630 --> 00:20:55.210 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLMAN: It is.

00:20:55.210 --> 00:20:56.240 align:middle line:90%
That's from my view.

00:20:56.240 --> 00:20:57.540 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: --into the life school.

00:20:57.540 --> 00:20:58.340 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:20:58.340 --> 00:20:59.640 align:middle line:90%
And then the second purpose?

00:20:59.640 --> 00:21:01.400 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: The second
purpose is what we normally

00:21:01.400 --> 00:21:02.310 align:middle line:90%
think of our purpose.

00:21:02.310 --> 00:21:03.560 align:middle line:90%
What is my career?

00:21:03.560 --> 00:21:04.970 align:middle line:90%
What is my calling?

00:21:04.970 --> 00:21:08.550 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes they're the same
thing in your case, in mine.

00:21:08.550 --> 00:21:11.180 align:middle line:84%
But for many people,
they have a career.

00:21:11.180 --> 00:21:12.110 align:middle line:90%
It's appropriate.

00:21:12.110 --> 00:21:14.840 align:middle line:84%
The primary purpose of a
career is to make an income.

00:21:14.840 --> 00:21:15.890 align:middle line:90%
We may like our career.

00:21:15.890 --> 00:21:18.002 align:middle line:84%
We may have people we
like, we work with.

00:21:18.002 --> 00:21:19.460 align:middle line:84%
But if we weren't
making any money,

00:21:19.460 --> 00:21:20.690 align:middle line:84%
we'd have to find
something else.

00:21:20.690 --> 00:21:21.140 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:21:21.140 --> 00:21:23.540 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: It's to support
ourselves and our family,

00:21:23.540 --> 00:21:25.470 align:middle line:84%
whereas a calling is
something we would do,

00:21:25.470 --> 00:21:27.030 align:middle line:90%
even if we weren't paid for it.

00:21:27.030 --> 00:21:28.490 align:middle line:90%
It's in our discretionary time.

00:21:28.490 --> 00:21:31.470 align:middle line:84%
Could be a hobby or
something we're moved to do.

00:21:31.470 --> 00:21:34.070 align:middle line:84%
And sometimes they become
the same, and they meld.

00:21:34.070 --> 00:21:35.670 align:middle line:90%
Other times they're separate.

00:21:35.670 --> 00:21:39.030 align:middle line:84%
But that's the second purpose
is getting more clarity.

00:21:39.030 --> 00:21:42.140 align:middle line:84%
And in several of my books,
I give specific methods

00:21:42.140 --> 00:21:45.540 align:middle line:84%
to become more clear on what's
the most appropriate work.

00:21:45.540 --> 00:21:47.870 align:middle line:84%
Because we can make
good money doing what

00:21:47.870 --> 00:21:51.010 align:middle line:84%
we enjoy or find suitable
while serving other people.

00:21:51.010 --> 00:21:52.760 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, you hear
that a lot, though,

00:21:52.760 --> 00:21:54.870 align:middle line:84%
is that this is my
spiritual practice,

00:21:54.870 --> 00:21:56.550 align:middle line:84%
and I'd like to make
more money from it.

00:21:56.550 --> 00:21:57.350 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLMAN: Right.

00:21:57.350 --> 00:21:58.880 align:middle line:90%
And if we can, that's great.

00:21:58.880 --> 00:22:02.250 align:middle line:84%
But some people-- it's playing
guitar or doing a sport.

00:22:02.250 --> 00:22:03.050 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Or singing.

00:22:03.050 --> 00:22:06.480 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: Or singing, or
dancing, or art, or writing.

00:22:06.480 --> 00:22:08.310 align:middle line:84%
But if we love doing
it, keep doing it.

00:22:08.310 --> 00:22:12.170 align:middle line:84%
And one day, perhaps an
income may be generated.

00:22:12.170 --> 00:22:13.910 align:middle line:90%
But meanwhile, my agents--

00:22:13.910 --> 00:22:16.460 align:middle line:84%
when I sold my first
book, I remember.

00:22:16.460 --> 00:22:17.750 align:middle line:90%
I never forgot what they said.

00:22:17.750 --> 00:22:19.800 align:middle line:90%
Don't quit your day job yet.

00:22:19.800 --> 00:22:23.390 align:middle line:84%
So we need a day job as well,
so we're not a starving artist.

00:22:23.390 --> 00:22:26.120 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Did you sell the
first book to a publisher?

00:22:26.120 --> 00:22:27.595 align:middle line:90%
Or did you self-publish it?

00:22:27.595 --> 00:22:28.970 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: I sold
to a publisher.

00:22:28.970 --> 00:22:29.450 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Did?

00:22:29.450 --> 00:22:31.120 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: I didn't
know what an agent was.

00:22:31.120 --> 00:22:32.860 align:middle line:84%
They said, you need to
send this to an agent,

00:22:32.860 --> 00:22:33.770 align:middle line:90%
so I found somebody.

00:22:33.770 --> 00:22:35.412 align:middle line:84%
And they were
willing to read it.

00:22:35.412 --> 00:22:36.620 align:middle line:90%
And they took a chance on it.

00:22:36.620 --> 00:22:39.590 align:middle line:90%
And it sold and sold modestly.

00:22:39.590 --> 00:22:40.970 align:middle line:90%
And I went from there.

00:22:40.970 --> 00:22:43.290 align:middle line:84%
But word of mouth is a
wonderful, magical thing

00:22:43.290 --> 00:22:44.090 align:middle line:90%
when it happens.

00:22:44.090 --> 00:22:45.340 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: When it's a good book.

00:22:45.340 --> 00:22:46.280 align:middle line:90%
Yes, absolutely.

00:22:46.280 --> 00:22:47.420 align:middle line:90%
OK, do we get to the third?

00:22:47.420 --> 00:22:50.090 align:middle line:84%
Because I found this
article in HuffPost.

00:22:50.090 --> 00:22:54.890 align:middle line:84%
And it was about the top 10
things people want in life,

00:22:54.890 --> 00:22:56.430 align:middle line:90%
but can't find.

00:22:56.430 --> 00:23:00.010 align:middle line:84%
And the top five things
had to do with purpose.

00:23:00.010 --> 00:23:02.220 align:middle line:84%
I mean, it's always
been an issue.

00:23:02.220 --> 00:23:04.530 align:middle line:90%
It's such an odd term--

00:23:04.530 --> 00:23:05.330 align:middle line:90%
purpose.

00:23:05.330 --> 00:23:05.900 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLMAN: Yes.

00:23:05.900 --> 00:23:08.233 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And it really, I
think, is up to the individual.

00:23:08.233 --> 00:23:09.312 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLMAN: It is.

00:23:09.312 --> 00:23:10.520 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: So what is the third?

00:23:10.520 --> 00:23:13.378 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: Well,
there are thousands

00:23:13.378 --> 00:23:15.170 align:middle line:84%
of purposes that appear
to different people

00:23:15.170 --> 00:23:16.370 align:middle line:90%
at different times.

00:23:16.370 --> 00:23:19.010 align:middle line:84%
But just as we divide
the days of the year

00:23:19.010 --> 00:23:21.610 align:middle line:84%
into four seasons and
the points on a compass

00:23:21.610 --> 00:23:24.920 align:middle line:84%
into four primary directions,
by looking at our life

00:23:24.920 --> 00:23:28.100 align:middle line:84%
through learning life's lessons,
through career and calling.

00:23:28.100 --> 00:23:31.550 align:middle line:84%
And the third purpose is
finding our life path.

00:23:31.550 --> 00:23:33.080 align:middle line:90%
It's like a hidden calling.

00:23:33.080 --> 00:23:34.740 align:middle line:90%
Most people are not clear.

00:23:34.740 --> 00:23:37.700 align:middle line:84%
They're stumbling in the dark,
wondering why they're not

00:23:37.700 --> 00:23:40.100 align:middle line:90%
feeling on track entirely.

00:23:40.100 --> 00:23:44.120 align:middle line:84%
And that's what an unusual
mentor I called the warrior

00:23:44.120 --> 00:23:50.240 align:middle line:84%
priest who taught me this system
for helping clarify one's life

00:23:50.240 --> 00:23:51.090 align:middle line:90%
path.

00:23:51.090 --> 00:23:52.460 align:middle line:90%
So it's another kind of purpose.

00:23:52.460 --> 00:23:54.320 align:middle line:84%
And that's what I
feature in "The Life

00:23:54.320 --> 00:23:55.430 align:middle line:90%
You Were Born to Live."

00:23:55.430 --> 00:23:58.730 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So it's a bigger
overarching theme in your life?

00:23:58.730 --> 00:23:59.980 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLMAN: It is.

00:23:59.980 --> 00:24:01.170 align:middle line:90%
It's a bigger theme.

00:24:01.170 --> 00:24:03.920 align:middle line:84%
It's what we learn
through relationships,

00:24:03.920 --> 00:24:06.290 align:middle line:84%
and through our work,
and through daily life.

00:24:06.290 --> 00:24:08.540 align:middle line:90%
We start to clarify.

00:24:08.540 --> 00:24:10.490 align:middle line:90%
Am I here to express myself?

00:24:10.490 --> 00:24:13.790 align:middle line:84%
Am I here to use
my creative energy?

00:24:13.790 --> 00:24:15.650 align:middle line:84%
Am I here to learn
to trust myself?

00:24:15.650 --> 00:24:19.810 align:middle line:84%
Different people have more acute
points in these various areas.

00:24:19.810 --> 00:24:21.600 align:middle line:84%
And there are 45
different life paths--

00:24:21.600 --> 00:24:22.400 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:24:22.400 --> 00:24:25.765 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: --for people born
since 1750 to the present day.

00:24:25.765 --> 00:24:27.350 align:middle line:90%
And so the book covers them all.

00:24:27.350 --> 00:24:31.050 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And what
about after 2000s?

00:24:31.050 --> 00:24:33.720 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: Well, there are some
individuals born after 2000

00:24:33.720 --> 00:24:35.970 align:middle line:84%
who have a single-digit
birth number.

00:24:35.970 --> 00:24:39.180 align:middle line:84%
And I explained in the new
edition of the book, which

00:24:39.180 --> 00:24:42.480 align:middle line:84%
came out recently,
why that's important,

00:24:42.480 --> 00:24:45.515 align:middle line:84%
and what master numbers
really mean, and so on.

00:24:45.515 --> 00:24:48.030 align:middle line:84%
And again, people say,
but explain it to me.

00:24:48.030 --> 00:24:49.620 align:middle line:90%
Scientifically, I can't.

00:24:49.620 --> 00:24:50.890 align:middle line:90%
But I do know it's accurate.

00:24:50.890 --> 00:24:51.690 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Accurate.

00:24:51.690 --> 00:24:52.050 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:24:52.050 --> 00:24:53.610 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: And
it's a useful tool

00:24:53.610 --> 00:24:55.525 align:middle line:90%
for understanding ourselves.

00:24:55.525 --> 00:24:56.400 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It always is.

00:24:56.400 --> 00:24:58.740 align:middle line:84%
It's a personality
test, essentially,

00:24:58.740 --> 00:25:02.310 align:middle line:84%
is when you look at
mine, is the life path 8.

00:25:02.310 --> 00:25:03.763 align:middle line:90%
And in various systems--

00:25:03.763 --> 00:25:05.430 align:middle line:84%
you could look at it
in various systems.

00:25:05.430 --> 00:25:07.440 align:middle line:90%
It all says the same thing.

00:25:07.440 --> 00:25:10.500 align:middle line:84%
It talks about having--
being goal oriented,

00:25:10.500 --> 00:25:14.340 align:middle line:84%
and having a mission in
life, and really moving

00:25:14.340 --> 00:25:15.390 align:middle line:90%
towards that mission.

00:25:15.390 --> 00:25:17.700 align:middle line:84%
Even if you look at my
birth sign, Capricorn,

00:25:17.700 --> 00:25:20.880 align:middle line:84%
it's climbing the mountain
to get to the mission,

00:25:20.880 --> 00:25:22.170 align:middle line:90%
that it's interesting.

00:25:22.170 --> 00:25:25.440 align:middle line:84%
So it does give you
a way of defining

00:25:25.440 --> 00:25:27.130 align:middle line:90%
your path a little bit more.

00:25:27.130 --> 00:25:27.930 align:middle line:90%
It's a guide.

00:25:27.930 --> 00:25:30.630 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: I'd like to think
of it as a foundation for life.

00:25:30.630 --> 00:25:33.420 align:middle line:84%
Once you understand
that, anything you--

00:25:33.420 --> 00:25:35.140 align:middle line:84%
whether it's dealing
with finances,

00:25:35.140 --> 00:25:36.490 align:middle line:90%
health, relationships.

00:25:36.490 --> 00:25:39.660 align:middle line:84%
And it's all covered in
the book-- those aspects.

00:25:39.660 --> 00:25:41.520 align:middle line:84%
You start to
understand how better

00:25:41.520 --> 00:25:42.900 align:middle line:90%
to approach those things.

00:25:42.900 --> 00:25:45.420 align:middle line:84%
I mean, the reading-- this
warrior priest did for me when

00:25:45.420 --> 00:25:47.430 align:middle line:90%
I was first exposed to this.

00:25:47.430 --> 00:25:48.590 align:middle line:90%
I said, are you a psychic?

00:25:48.590 --> 00:25:51.370 align:middle line:84%
He said, no, but I've been
trained to know where to look.

00:25:51.370 --> 00:25:53.220 align:middle line:84%
And that's what I
share with people.

00:25:53.220 --> 00:25:55.920 align:middle line:84%
Many people say, Dan, I wish
I had a mentor like Socrates.

00:25:55.920 --> 00:25:57.060 align:middle line:90%
And I go, you do.

00:25:57.060 --> 00:25:59.070 align:middle line:90%
That's why I wrote the book.

00:25:59.070 --> 00:26:02.110 align:middle line:84%
And we all find who we need
at the time we need it.

00:26:02.110 --> 00:26:02.910 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:26:02.910 --> 00:26:06.420 align:middle line:84%
And you can also look up other
people's life path numbers

00:26:06.420 --> 00:26:09.600 align:middle line:84%
