Do you mind?

00:29:31.980 --> 00:29:32.290 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLMAN: Sure.

00:29:32.290 --> 00:29:32.800 align:middle line:90%
Be happy to.

00:29:32.800 --> 00:29:33.750 align:middle line:84%
Should I stand up
here and do it?

00:29:33.750 --> 00:29:34.500 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Awesome.

00:29:34.500 --> 00:29:36.333 align:middle line:84%
I don't know if we can
do the standing part.

00:29:36.333 --> 00:29:38.950 align:middle line:90%
Can you do it sitting?

00:29:38.950 --> 00:29:39.950 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLMAN: Probably not.

00:29:39.950 --> 00:29:42.040 align:middle line:84%
It's designed-- I mean,
there are some movements

00:29:42.040 --> 00:29:42.840 align:middle line:90%
you could do.

00:29:42.840 --> 00:29:44.790 align:middle line:84%
But the first one is
the stretch back--

00:29:44.790 --> 00:29:46.740 align:middle line:84%
a profound, deep
stretch back and then a

00:29:46.740 --> 00:29:49.360 align:middle line:84%
swing down, where you actually
are standing up with your legs

00:29:49.360 --> 00:29:50.160 align:middle line:90%
straight.

00:29:50.160 --> 00:29:51.900 align:middle line:90%
And you do a momentary stretch.

00:29:51.900 --> 00:29:54.590 align:middle line:84%
This one is a
squat-down side stretch

00:29:54.590 --> 00:29:57.660 align:middle line:84%
where you fill the lungs
up and stretch sideways.

00:29:57.660 --> 00:30:01.380 align:middle line:84%
Then we work down the body with
a neck release and shoulder

00:30:01.380 --> 00:30:03.930 align:middle line:90%
rolls to open up tension here.

00:30:03.930 --> 00:30:08.910 align:middle line:84%
And then a spine swing for the
lower spine abdominals and then

00:30:08.910 --> 00:30:12.660 align:middle line:84%
something called Elvis Pelvis
for the deep pelvic muscles.

00:30:12.660 --> 00:30:14.160 align:middle line:84%
And then one called
Heaven and Earth

00:30:14.160 --> 00:30:16.800 align:middle line:84%
where you stretch up and
down, balancing on one leg

00:30:16.800 --> 00:30:17.760 align:middle line:90%
momentarily.

00:30:17.760 --> 00:30:19.740 align:middle line:90%
That gives you an idea about it.

00:30:19.740 --> 00:30:22.440 align:middle line:84%
And there's others more
for cardiovascular.

00:30:22.440 --> 00:30:24.292 align:middle line:84%
But it's a workout
anyone can do.

00:30:24.292 --> 00:30:25.500 align:middle line:90%
It's like a suit of clothing.

00:30:25.500 --> 00:30:26.782 align:middle line:90%
You tailor it for yourself.

00:30:26.782 --> 00:30:28.240 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And where
do you find that?

00:30:28.240 --> 00:30:29.070 align:middle line:90%
Where's the workout?

00:30:29.070 --> 00:30:31.403 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: People can go to
peacefulwarrior.com and look

00:30:31.403 --> 00:30:33.270 align:middle line:84%
for my online courses,
and it's all there.

00:30:33.270 --> 00:30:34.140 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That is so cool.

00:30:34.140 --> 00:30:35.390 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLMAN: And it can be done.

