it took me three weeks,

00:31:50.070 --> 00:31:52.080 align:middle line:90%
a very discouraging practice.

00:31:52.080 --> 00:31:55.320 align:middle line:84%
If anybody has tried to ride
one, it feels impossible.

00:31:55.320 --> 00:31:57.480 align:middle line:90%
I felt like a klutz.

00:31:57.480 --> 00:31:59.520 align:middle line:84%
After one week, a
little bit of progress.

00:31:59.520 --> 00:32:01.210 align:middle line:90%
Two weeks-- a little bit more.

00:32:01.210 --> 00:32:02.700 align:middle line:90%
But then it clicked.

00:32:02.700 --> 00:32:04.710 align:middle line:84%
And by the third week, I
was doing figure eights

00:32:04.710 --> 00:32:06.150 align:middle line:90%
around the courts.

00:32:06.150 --> 00:32:09.090 align:middle line:84%
And the reason I mention
this is because I

00:32:09.090 --> 00:32:10.390 align:middle line:90%
learned two things from that.

00:32:10.390 --> 00:32:14.790 align:middle line:84%
One is everything is difficult
until it becomes easy.

00:32:14.790 --> 00:32:16.030 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: True.

00:32:16.030 --> 00:32:17.625 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: So people hit
something, and it's difficult.

00:32:17.625 --> 00:32:19.083 align:middle line:84%
And they go, oh,
this isn't for me.

00:32:19.083 --> 00:32:20.580 align:middle line:90%
I can't do this.

00:32:20.580 --> 00:32:22.180 align:middle line:90%
But just persist through it.

00:32:22.180 --> 00:32:22.980 align:middle line:90%
That's what I did.

00:32:22.980 --> 00:32:26.130 align:middle line:84%
I came back every day
and kept doing it.

00:32:26.130 --> 00:32:27.780 align:middle line:90%
And then something happened.

00:32:27.780 --> 00:32:28.980 align:middle line:90%
But the second thing--

00:32:28.980 --> 00:32:31.320 align:middle line:84%
there are days in
a relationship,

00:32:31.320 --> 00:32:34.590 align:middle line:84%
learning to ride a unicycle, in
other fields of endeavor where

00:32:34.590 --> 00:32:37.500 align:middle line:84%
everything seems to fall
apart, where you're worse

00:32:37.500 --> 00:32:39.100 align:middle line:90%
than you were days before.

00:32:39.100 --> 00:32:39.900 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:32:39.900 --> 00:32:41.275 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: But
those are the days

00:32:41.275 --> 00:32:43.770 align:middle line:84%
where it's going from the
front brain to the back brain.

00:32:43.770 --> 00:32:46.470 align:middle line:84%
Those are the days where
it's becoming automatic.

00:32:46.470 --> 00:32:49.655 align:middle line:84%
And it is-- the whole body is
confused-- the mind, the body.

00:32:49.655 --> 00:32:51.780 align:middle line:84%
But usually, that's when
the learning is happening.

00:32:51.780 --> 00:32:54.550 align:middle line:84%
And there's often a
breakthrough the next day.

00:32:54.550 --> 00:32:58.200 align:middle line:84%
So in a relationship crisis,
if you persist through it,

00:32:58.200 --> 00:33:01.380 align:middle line:84%
you can often break through
to new levels of intimacy

00:33:01.380 --> 00:33:04.145 align:middle line:84%
the same way you can
learning to ride a unicycle.

00:33:04.145 --> 00:33:06.060 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: So stick with something.

00:33:06.060 --> 00:33:07.470 align:middle line:84%
Maybe even try
something that you

00:33:07.470 --> 00:33:09.450 align:middle line:84%
don't know you're going to be
good at, like maybe juggling.

00:33:09.450 --> 00:33:10.250 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLMAN: Sure.

00:33:10.250 --> 00:33:12.510 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And just stick
with it as a hobby

00:33:12.510 --> 00:33:14.040 align:middle line:84%
until you can
actually master it.

00:33:14.040 --> 00:33:14.400 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLMAN: We're not supposed--

00:33:14.400 --> 00:33:15.317 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Not master it.

00:33:15.317 --> 00:33:17.250 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: --to be
confident at the start.

00:33:17.250 --> 00:33:19.110 align:middle line:84%
We're not supposed
to be confident.

00:33:19.110 --> 00:33:21.310 align:middle line:90%
Competence breeds confidence.

00:33:21.310 --> 00:33:23.190 align:middle line:84%
But if we keep
practicing anything,

00:33:23.190 --> 00:33:25.270 align:middle line:90%
you develop a certain expertise.

00:33:25.270 --> 00:33:27.090 align:middle line:84%
That's the secret
if there is one,

00:33:27.090 --> 00:33:29.440 align:middle line:90%
is keep doing it over time.

00:33:29.440 --> 00:33:30.240 align:middle line:90%
We get better.

00:33:30.240 --> 00:33:32.520 align:middle line:84%
And then we start to
feel the confidence.

00:33:32.520 --> 00:33:34.680 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And doesn't
the brain love newness?

00:33:34.680 --> 00:33:35.940 align:middle line:90%
Creates all that dopamine?

00:33:35.940 --> 00:33:36.750 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLMAN: It does.

00:33:36.750 --> 00:33:37.560 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely.

00:33:37.560 --> 00:33:38.250 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Loves new things.

00:33:38.250 --> 00:33:39.780 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLMAN: And every day is new.

00:33:39.780 --> 00:33:42.450 align:middle line:84%
I taught a thousand seat
drops on the trampoline--

00:33:42.450 --> 00:33:43.650 align:middle line:90%
just seat drops.

00:33:43.650 --> 00:33:45.780 align:middle line:84%
But I never taught the
same one, because each one

00:33:45.780 --> 00:33:48.540 align:middle line:84%
is a different person,
different circumstance.

00:33:48.540 --> 00:33:50.550 align:middle line:84%
We think-- most people--
maybe they're bored,

00:33:50.550 --> 00:33:52.150 align:middle line:84%
or they're
traumatized, or bored.

00:33:52.150 --> 00:33:52.950 align:middle line:90%
They try something.

00:33:52.950 --> 00:33:53.650 align:middle line:90%
I can't do this.

00:33:53.650 --> 00:33:54.010 align:middle line:90%
I can't do it.

00:33:54.010 --> 00:33:56.520 align:middle line:84%
Then they do it right once,
and they go, OK, now I'm bored.

00:33:56.520 --> 00:33:57.320 align:middle line:90%
Let's move on.

00:33:57.320 --> 00:33:58.430 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:33:58.430 --> 00:34:00.300 align:middle line:84%
But we never do the
same thing twice.

00:34:00.300 --> 00:34:03.480 align:middle line:84%
It's always-- I'm still refining
the Peaceable Warrior Workout.

00:34:03.480 --> 00:34:06.040 align:middle line:84%
After 30 years, I'm getting
a little bit better.

00:34:06.040 --> 00:34:06.840 align:middle line:90%
Small points.

00:34:06.840 --> 00:34:11.010 align:middle line:84%
So I once asked Socrates what
his secret of living was.

00:34:11.010 --> 00:34:13.530 align:middle line:84%
And he said, Dan, you
practice gymnastics.

00:34:13.530 --> 00:34:15.719 align:middle line:90%
I practice everything.

00:34:15.719 --> 00:34:18.270 align:middle line:84%
And the idea of practicing
everything we do-- breathing,

00:34:18.270 --> 00:34:20.190 align:middle line:90%
walking, standing--

00:34:20.190 --> 00:34:23.219 align:middle line:84%
brings us into that
flow, that absorption.

00:34:23.219 --> 00:34:24.600 align:middle line:90%
We're not just doing the dishes.

00:34:24.600 --> 00:34:26.165 align:middle line:90%
We're practicing the dishes.

00:34:26.165 --> 00:34:27.540 align:middle line:84%
We're not just
doing the laundry.

00:34:27.540 --> 00:34:29.469 align:middle line:84%
We're folding it more
neatly than we did.

00:34:29.469 --> 00:34:31.510 align:middle line:90%
We're practicing our signature.

00:34:31.510 --> 00:34:34.239 align:middle line:84%
And by doing that, it
brings us into this--

00:34:34.239 --> 00:34:37.290 align:middle line:84%
really this state of absorption
in the present moment.

00:34:37.290 --> 00:34:38.949 align:middle line:90%
It becomes very zen-like.

00:34:38.949 --> 00:34:41.530 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I was just going to say
it's just like a zen master.

00:34:41.530 --> 00:34:42.429 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLMAN: Yes.

00:34:42.429 --> 00:34:43.765 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Is that how
you live your life?

00:34:43.765 --> 00:34:44.920 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: Well, that's
what I strive to do--

00:34:44.920 --> 00:34:45.219 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah, of course.

00:34:45.219 --> 00:34:46.870 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLMAN: --like anybody.

00:34:46.870 --> 00:34:48.429 align:middle line:90%
I have moments.

00:34:48.429 --> 00:34:49.870 align:middle line:90%
Life is a series of moments.

00:34:49.870 --> 00:34:52.406 align:middle line:84%
But, yes, that-- someone
once said, have you

00:34:52.406 --> 00:34:54.489 align:middle line:84%
mastered everything you
write about in your books?

00:34:54.489 --> 00:34:56.139 align:middle line:90%
The answer is no, I haven't.

00:34:56.139 --> 00:34:58.015 align:middle line:90%
But I'm sincerely practicing.

00:34:58.015 --> 00:35:00.340 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, there's the
book, "The Hidden School--"

00:35:00.340 --> 00:35:00.800 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLMAN: Yes.

00:35:00.800 --> 00:35:02.383 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: --basically
talking about life

00:35:02.383 --> 00:35:04.320 align:middle line:90%
is your hidden school, right?

00:35:04.320 --> 00:35:06.610 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: Right--
for all of us.

00:35:06.610 --> 00:35:09.385 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Tell me a little
bit more about that book.

00:35:09.385 --> 00:35:12.910 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: Well, in that
book, I build the foundation

00:35:12.910 --> 00:35:14.350 align:middle line:90%
beneath the foundation.

00:35:14.350 --> 00:35:17.200 align:middle line:84%
It's more of an
advanced teaching.

00:35:17.200 --> 00:35:20.290 align:middle line:84%
But I took great care
in writing it clearly.

00:35:20.290 --> 00:35:23.320 align:middle line:84%
Andr Gide once said, everything
that needs to be said has

00:35:23.320 --> 00:35:24.467 align:middle line:90%
already been said.

00:35:24.467 --> 00:35:26.800 align:middle line:84%
But it needs to be said again,
because no one was really

00:35:26.800 --> 00:35:27.990 align:middle line:90%
paying attention.

00:35:27.990 --> 00:35:28.780 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Or in a different way.

00:35:28.780 --> 00:35:30.050 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLMAN: In a different way.

00:35:30.050 --> 00:35:33.220 align:middle line:84%
And in this way, I
help people reconcile

00:35:33.220 --> 00:35:35.830 align:middle line:84%
truths that happen at
the conventional level

00:35:35.830 --> 00:35:37.180 align:middle line:90%
like we're separate selves.

00:35:37.180 --> 00:35:39.700 align:middle line:84%
At the conventional level
of life, if I stub my toe,

00:35:39.700 --> 00:35:42.547 align:middle line:84%
it doesn't hurt you, unless
you're highly empathic.

00:35:42.547 --> 00:35:44.380 align:middle line:84%
So we're separate at
the conventional level.

00:35:44.380 --> 00:35:47.800 align:middle line:84%
But at the transcendental
level, that thing

00:35:47.800 --> 00:35:50.960 align:middle line:84%
we strive for through religion
and spiritual practice--

00:35:50.960 --> 00:35:52.630 align:middle line:90%
we are all one.

00:35:52.630 --> 00:35:55.270 align:middle line:84%
And it helps reconcile
these apparent paradoxes

00:35:55.270 --> 00:35:57.310 align:middle line:90%
that sound opposite.

00:35:57.310 --> 00:35:59.920 align:middle line:84%
Death is real, yet
death is an illusion.

00:35:59.920 --> 00:36:02.290 align:middle line:84%
Time is real and yet,
there is no time.

00:36:02.290 --> 00:36:05.060 align:middle line:84%
We always live in the eternal
present, the eternal present,

00:36:05.060 --> 00:36:06.520 align:middle line:90%
the eternal present.

00:36:06.520 --> 00:36:08.730 align:middle line:90%
So how can those both be true?

00:36:08.730 --> 00:36:09.530 align:middle line:90%
Well, they are.

00:36:09.530 --> 00:36:11.530 align:middle line:84%
But it depends on what
level we're coming from--

00:36:11.530 --> 00:36:13.480 align:middle line:90%
the conventional--

00:36:13.480 --> 00:36:16.030 align:middle line:84%
living our daily
life or those moments

00:36:16.030 --> 00:36:20.080 align:middle line:84%
we can step to the mountain top
and look from the big picture.

00:36:20.080 --> 00:36:22.720 align:middle line:84%
And we see a different
level of truth, which

00:36:22.720 --> 00:36:24.700 align:middle line:90%
brings great peace and relief.

00:36:24.700 --> 00:36:26.590 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: How long after
"Peaceful Warrior"

00:36:26.590 --> 00:36:28.560 align:middle line:90%
did you write "Hidden School?"

00:36:28.560 --> 00:36:29.830 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLMAN: About 37 years.

00:36:29.830 --> 00:36:30.630 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:36:30.630 --> 00:36:33.310 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: I wasn't ready
to write it until recently.

00:36:33.310 --> 00:36:36.450 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And you really wanted
to bring in the depth of what

00:36:36.450 --> 00:36:37.250 align:middle line:90%
you'd learned.

00:36:37.250 --> 00:36:38.050 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLMAN: Right.

00:36:38.050 --> 00:36:39.550 align:middle line:84%
It's actually an
adventure story.

00:36:39.550 --> 00:36:41.510 align:middle line:84%
But through-- near
the end of the story,

00:36:41.510 --> 00:36:43.463 align:middle line:84%
that's when these
revelations come.

00:36:43.463 --> 00:36:45.880 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Let's take a look here
at the video of "The Hidden

00:36:45.880 --> 00:36:46.680 align:middle line:90%
School."

00:36:46.680 --> 00:36:53.830 align:middle line:90%


00:36:53.830 --> 00:36:55.990 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: On the subway
and here in New York City,

00:36:55.990 --> 00:37:00.100 align:middle line:84%
I did a 4-Minute Meditation,
which I do introduce

00:37:00.100 --> 00:37:02.080 align:middle line:90%
in "The Hidden School."

00:37:02.080 --> 00:37:06.310 align:middle line:84%
And it reminds me
what's important in life

00:37:06.310 --> 00:37:09.580 align:middle line:84%
and helps me to appreciate
each day and each moment.

00:37:09.580 --> 00:37:15.820 align:middle line:84%
We can get taken in and absorbed
by the duties of daily life.

00:37:15.820 --> 00:37:18.580 align:middle line:84%
Once in a while, it's
good to step back as if

00:37:18.580 --> 00:37:20.920 align:middle line:84%
going from down in the
weeds, up to a mountain top.

00:37:20.920 --> 00:37:23.440 align:middle line:84%
Because everything looks
better in a panorama

00:37:23.440 --> 00:37:24.950 align:middle line:90%
from the distance.

00:37:24.950 --> 00:37:28.480 align:middle line:84%
So these explorations remind
us of life's bigger picture,

00:37:28.480 --> 00:37:31.780 align:middle line:84%
what we're really doing
here and here to do.

00:37:31.780 --> 00:37:34.870 align:middle line:84%
There's a term in
Japan called satori

00:37:34.870 --> 00:37:39.580 align:middle line:84%
when the mind, and the goals,
and the body, and the emotions

00:37:39.580 --> 00:37:40.835 align:middle line:90%
are all aligned.

00:37:40.835 --> 00:37:43.268 align:middle line:90%
And there's a power in that.

00:37:43.268 --> 00:37:45.310 align:middle line:84%
Because often, we do one
thing and think another.

00:37:45.310 --> 00:37:46.727 align:middle line:84%
Many of us have
heard that saying.

00:37:46.727 --> 00:37:49.450 align:middle line:84%
When the student is ready,
the teacher appears.

00:37:49.450 --> 00:37:51.700 align:middle line:84%
However, many
misunderstand that saying.

00:37:51.700 --> 00:37:54.280 align:middle line:84%
What it actually means
is when the student is

00:37:54.280 --> 00:37:56.440 align:middle line:84%
ready or really
paying attention,

00:37:56.440 --> 00:37:59.290 align:middle line:90%
the teacher appears everywhere.

00:37:59.290 --> 00:38:00.820 align:middle line:84%
I learned a profound
lesson one day,

00:38:00.820 --> 00:38:03.640 align:middle line:90%
watching a cloud ride the wind.

00:38:03.640 --> 00:38:05.280 align:middle line:90%
And I had so much to do.

00:38:05.280 --> 00:38:06.850 align:middle line:90%
My breath was shallow.

00:38:06.850 --> 00:38:07.960 align:middle line:90%
I felt pressured.

00:38:07.960 --> 00:38:10.090 align:middle line:84%
And I happened to
look out the window.

00:38:10.090 --> 00:38:13.120 align:middle line:84%
And I saw a cloud not
trying to race the wind,

00:38:13.120 --> 00:38:16.030 align:middle line:84%
but just floating along
with the pace of the wind.

00:38:16.030 --> 00:38:18.860 align:middle line:84%
In that moment, I
took a deep breath.

00:38:18.860 --> 00:38:20.650 align:middle line:90%
I calmed down.

00:38:20.650 --> 00:38:23.740 align:middle line:84%
And I did everything I
needed to do that afternoon,

00:38:23.740 --> 00:38:28.090 align:middle line:84%
but quiet in a natural
pace like that cloud.

00:38:28.090 --> 00:38:32.290 align:middle line:10%
That question of why people
may benefit from a deeper

00:38:32.290 --> 00:38:37.470 align:middle line:10%
philosophical or spiritual
exploration is a profound one

00:38:37.470 --> 00:38:38.950 align:middle line:10%
and I think important
for all of us

00:38:38.950 --> 00:38:43.829 align:middle line:10%
to consider, at least
in moments of our lives.

00:38:43.829 --> 00:38:46.120 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I learn so
much from clouds.

00:38:46.120 --> 00:38:47.513 align:middle line:90%
I do.

00:38:47.513 --> 00:38:49.180 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: And trees
bending in the wind

00:38:49.180 --> 00:38:51.310 align:middle line:90%
and streams flowing downhill.

00:38:51.310 --> 00:38:52.660 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Absolute.

00:38:52.660 --> 00:38:54.400 align:middle line:84%
I just did a video
of that this morning.

00:38:54.400 --> 00:38:55.220 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLMAN: Did you?

00:38:55.220 --> 00:38:56.020 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:38:56.020 --> 00:38:58.120 align:middle line:84%
If we could just
be like the stream

00:38:58.120 --> 00:39:02.170 align:middle line:84%
and go over the rocks, and
downstream, and flow like it

00:39:02.170 --> 00:39:03.180 align:middle line:90%
does.

00:39:03.180 --> 00:39:04.930 align:middle line:84%
It never thinks about,
oh, there's a rock.

00:39:04.930 --> 00:39:06.700 align:middle line:90%
I can't flow.

00:39:06.700 --> 00:39:08.640 align:middle line:84%
The rest of the
stream is still going.

00:39:08.640 --> 00:39:09.440 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLMAN: Yes.

00:39:09.440 --> 00:39:12.580 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah, it's interesting.

00:39:12.580 --> 00:39:15.730 align:middle line:84%
Do you recommend that
we go on a pilgrimage

00:39:15.730 --> 00:39:20.530 align:middle line:84%
or vacate our lives in order to
really, truly find ourselves?

00:39:20.530 --> 00:39:22.990 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: I think one of the
deeper truths that I found,

00:39:22.990 --> 00:39:26.770 align:middle line:84%
Lisa, is that we're
all on a pilgrimage.

00:39:26.770 --> 00:39:28.960 align:middle line:84%
Whether it's conscious
or not, we're

00:39:28.960 --> 00:39:32.290 align:middle line:84%
all on a spiritual quest in
this school of daily life.

00:39:32.290 --> 00:39:33.540 align:middle line:90%
We don't have to be elsewhere.

00:39:33.540 --> 00:39:34.500 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: So we don't?

00:39:34.500 --> 00:39:35.300 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLMAN: No.

00:39:35.300 --> 00:39:35.710 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:39:35.710 --> 00:39:37.180 align:middle line:84%
I mean, some people
like retreats.

00:39:37.180 --> 00:39:38.680 align:middle line:84%
That can be appropriate
or to take--

00:39:38.680 --> 00:39:38.790 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: But then--

00:39:38.790 --> 00:39:39.465 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLMAN: --some time.

00:39:39.465 --> 00:39:40.720 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: --you slam
back into your life.

00:39:40.720 --> 00:39:42.178 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: Back
into everyday life.

00:39:42.178 --> 00:39:43.600 align:middle line:90%
This is where we live.

00:39:43.600 --> 00:39:47.480 align:middle line:84%
So that's where the arena of
the peaceful warrior lies.

00:39:47.480 --> 00:39:48.730 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: And the hidden school.

00:39:48.730 --> 00:39:49.775 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: And
the hidden school.

00:39:49.775 --> 00:39:50.060 align:middle line:90%
And it's waiting--

00:39:50.060 --> 00:39:50.570 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: The hidden school is--

00:39:50.570 --> 00:39:50.860 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLMAN: --for us.

00:39:50.860 --> 00:39:51.580 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: --right here.

00:39:51.580 --> 00:39:52.955 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: Right
here, right now.

00:39:52.955 --> 00:39:54.910 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: You said
it's an adventure.

00:39:54.910 --> 00:39:56.395 align:middle line:90%
Tell me a little bit about that.

00:39:56.395 --> 00:39:58.883 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: Well, many people
undersell their own life.

00:39:58.883 --> 00:40:00.800 align:middle line:84%
They say, oh, Dan wrote
a book about his life.

00:40:00.800 --> 00:40:01.700 align:middle line:90%
It's so exciting.

00:40:01.700 --> 00:40:02.500 align:middle line:90%
What about mine?

00:40:02.500 --> 00:40:07.790 align:middle line:84%
But I emphasized always
that each of our stories

00:40:07.790 --> 00:40:08.590 align:middle line:90%
is our treasure.

00:40:08.590 --> 00:40:11.290 align:middle line:84%
Because there's not a
single story on the planet

00:40:11.290 --> 00:40:15.880 align:middle line:84%
exactly like yours, or mine,
or any of your viewers.

00:40:15.880 --> 00:40:17.710 align:middle line:90%
We're all unique.

00:40:17.710 --> 00:40:20.140 align:middle line:84%
And so we need to
value those stories.

00:40:20.140 --> 00:40:23.200 align:middle line:84%
Because we've all shown heroism
and courage in those stories.

00:40:23.200 --> 00:40:25.210 align:middle line:90%
We've all overcome adversity.

00:40:25.210 --> 00:40:27.260 align:middle line:84%
So that's why I say
it's an adventure.

00:40:27.260 --> 00:40:30.520 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't have to be
some movie we're watching.

00:40:30.520 --> 00:40:33.160 align:middle line:84%
It's happening to us right
now, but we sometimes

00:40:33.160 --> 00:40:34.990 align:middle line:90%
fail to appreciate it.

00:40:34.990 --> 00:40:39.010 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Do you know-- what
is your life purpose number?

00:40:39.010 --> 00:40:40.750 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLMAN: It's a 268.

00:40:40.750 --> 00:40:41.860 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:40:41.860 --> 00:40:44.680 align:middle line:84%
And what did that show
you about yourself?

00:40:44.680 --> 00:40:46.870 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: Well, the 2
really is about wanting

00:40:46.870 --> 00:40:49.510 align:middle line:90%
to help and support people.

00:40:49.510 --> 00:40:50.877 align:middle line:90%
It's a need to help people--

00:40:50.877 --> 00:40:51.960 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: And natural coach.

00:40:51.960 --> 00:40:54.510 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: --so wanting
to teach or coach.

00:40:54.510 --> 00:40:56.260 align:middle line:84%
One day I realized
that no matter how much

00:40:56.260 --> 00:40:58.640 align:middle line:84%
I improved myself, only
one person benefited.

00:40:58.640 --> 00:41:00.820 align:middle line:84%
But if I could somehow
reach out to other people--

00:41:00.820 --> 00:41:04.120 align:middle line:84%
so it went from gymnastics
into the arena of daily life,

00:41:04.120 --> 00:41:05.340 align:middle line:90%
as I said.

00:41:05.340 --> 00:41:08.110 align:middle line:90%
And the six high standards.

00:41:08.110 --> 00:41:09.730 align:middle line:84%
We can sometimes
beat ourselves up,

00:41:09.730 --> 00:41:13.720 align:middle line:84%
because we never achieved
what we thought or envisioned.

00:41:13.720 --> 00:41:16.480 align:middle line:84%
That castle in our mind
becomes a garden shed,

00:41:16.480 --> 00:41:18.410 align:middle line:90%
and we have to do renovations.

00:41:18.410 --> 00:41:21.380 align:middle line:84%
So that's the
perfectionist part.

00:41:21.380 --> 00:41:24.790 align:middle line:84%
And that's the 6, really, but
the vision of what's possible.

00:41:24.790 --> 00:41:27.250 align:middle line:84%
And the 8-- as you
indicated, it's

00:41:27.250 --> 00:41:29.860 align:middle line:84%
a drive to influence
people, to make

00:41:29.860 --> 00:41:33.200 align:middle line:84%
a difference, and a drive for
recognition in some sense, too.

00:41:33.200 --> 00:41:35.290 align:middle line:90%
That's part of it.

00:41:35.290 --> 00:41:38.830 align:middle line:90%
To learn our own power.

00:41:38.830 --> 00:41:44.480 align:middle line:84%
That's a big one, too, to really
own that in a quiet, real way.

00:41:44.480 --> 00:41:48.290 align:middle line:84%
So there are various
nuances of each number.

00:41:48.290 --> 00:41:51.020 align:middle line:84%
And I think Pythagoras was
the first to really ask,

00:41:51.020 --> 00:41:52.410 align:middle line:90%
do numbers have meaning?

00:41:52.410 --> 00:41:54.140 align:middle line:84%
What are the
archetypes of numbers?

00:41:54.140 --> 00:41:54.940 align:middle line:90%
And so--

00:41:54.940 --> 00:41:55.773 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's cool.

00:41:55.773 --> 00:41:57.910 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: --that's probably
the source of this--

00:41:57.910 --> 00:42:00.720 align:middle line:84%
ultimately of what I teach
in these various books

00:42:00.720 --> 00:42:01.520 align:middle line:90%
and in some of my--

00:42:01.520 --> 00:42:01.950 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's true.

00:42:01.950 --> 00:42:02.630 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLMAN: --workshops.

00:42:02.630 --> 00:42:04.240 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Numbers are--
they do have archetypes.

00:42:04.240 --> 00:42:05.610 align:middle line:84%
That's a really great
way of looking at it.

00:42:05.610 --> 00:42:07.090 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLMAN: Life is vibration.

00:42:07.090 --> 00:42:09.010 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: But are there
shadow sides to that?

00:42:09.010 --> 00:42:12.010 align:middle line:84%
So there's the perfectionism,
which can have a shadow side.

00:42:12.010 --> 00:42:15.210 align:middle line:84%
But what's the antidote
to perfectionism?

00:42:15.210 --> 00:42:17.560 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: One of the most
important parts of the book

00:42:17.560 --> 00:42:20.740 align:middle line:84%
are spiritual or universal
laws that I put in the book

00:42:20.740 --> 00:42:22.600 align:middle line:90%
to help overcome the hurdles.

00:42:22.600 --> 00:42:25.210 align:middle line:84%
Because every life
path has hurdles in it

00:42:25.210 --> 00:42:27.280 align:middle line:90%
as well as strengths.

00:42:27.280 --> 00:42:29.470 align:middle line:84%
In fact, I have a
section-- one paragraph

00:42:29.470 --> 00:42:31.630 align:middle line:84%
on what each life
path looks like when

00:42:31.630 --> 00:42:33.037 align:middle line:84%
it's being worked
in the positive

00:42:33.037 --> 00:42:35.120 align:middle line:84%
and what it looks like
when it's being worked more

00:42:35.120 --> 00:42:35.290 align:middle line:90%
in the negative.

00:42:35.290 --> 00:42:36.130 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: I like that.

00:42:36.130 --> 00:42:38.463 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: That's why two
people on the same life path--

00:42:38.463 --> 00:42:39.970 align:middle line:84%
their lives may
look very different.

00:42:39.970 --> 00:42:42.160 align:middle line:84%
Because one's-- it's
in a more mature,

00:42:42.160 --> 00:42:44.680 align:middle line:84%
developed way and
the other less so.

00:42:44.680 --> 00:42:49.390 align:middle line:84%
So these laws-- the law of
honesty, the law of process,

00:42:49.390 --> 00:42:51.777 align:middle line:90%
for example.

00:42:51.777 --> 00:42:53.110 align:middle line:90%
I know that sounds very general.

00:42:53.110 --> 00:42:55.300 align:middle line:84%
But when people look in
the book or on the app,

00:42:55.300 --> 00:42:57.040 align:middle line:84%
they can see specifically
how it relates

00:42:57.040 --> 00:42:59.985 align:middle line:84%
to their life and the issues
they're going through.

00:42:59.985 --> 00:43:02.110 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Would you say that
this is something that's

00:43:02.110 --> 00:43:04.540 align:middle line:84%
a tool that people
really could use

00:43:04.540 --> 00:43:08.530 align:middle line:84%
to further their path in
life or their relationships

00:43:08.530 --> 00:43:09.400 align:middle line:90%
with other people?

00:43:09.400 --> 00:43:10.317 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLMAN: Absolutely.

00:43:10.317 --> 00:43:12.708 align:middle line:84%
In fact, if somebody goes
to peacefulwarrior,com,

00:43:12.708 --> 00:43:14.500 align:middle line:84%
they don't just put in
their date of birth.

00:43:14.500 --> 00:43:16.330 align:middle line:84%
They can put in a
second date of birth

00:43:16.330 --> 00:43:18.940 align:middle line:84%
and a significant other,
a spouse, a friend.

00:43:18.940 --> 00:43:20.680 align:middle line:84%
And they see the
dynamic between them.

00:43:20.680 --> 00:43:21.550 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, that's great.

00:43:21.550 --> 00:43:22.240 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLMAN: It's all for free.

00:43:22.240 --> 00:43:23.140 align:middle line:90%
It's right there at the website.

00:43:23.140 --> 00:43:24.745 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: How did
you develop that?

00:43:24.745 --> 00:43:25.750 align:middle line:90%
That is cool.

00:43:25.750 --> 00:43:27.430 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: Well,
that was part of what

00:43:27.430 --> 00:43:30.880 align:middle line:84%
I learned from this mentor, and
I developed it over the years.

00:43:30.880 --> 00:43:32.650 align:middle line:90%
I only had 20 pages of notes.

00:43:32.650 --> 00:43:34.900 align:middle line:84%
And it developed into
a fairly big book.

00:43:34.900 --> 00:43:36.670 align:middle line:84%
After years of
working with people,

00:43:36.670 --> 00:43:38.860 align:middle line:84%
and doing readings, and
working with the system,

00:43:38.860 --> 00:43:40.360 align:middle line:90%
new insights came.

00:43:40.360 --> 00:43:43.000 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I think that's
a great story, also,

00:43:43.000 --> 00:43:46.390 align:middle line:90%
of recreating yourself.

00:43:46.390 --> 00:43:48.070 align:middle line:90%
You really did.

00:43:48.070 --> 00:43:49.960 align:middle line:84%
You took something that
meant so much to you

00:43:49.960 --> 00:43:51.070 align:middle line:90%
and made such an impact.

00:43:51.070 --> 00:43:54.790 align:middle line:84%
But 25 years later,
what do I do with this?

00:43:54.790 --> 00:43:56.562 align:middle line:90%
And where does it take me?

00:43:56.562 --> 00:43:58.270 align:middle line:84%
And I'm sure you've
been asked questions.

00:43:58.270 --> 00:44:00.560 align:middle line:84%
Well, why did you turn
into numerology after this?

00:44:00.560 --> 00:44:01.360 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLMAN: Right.

00:44:01.360 --> 00:44:03.340 align:middle line:84%
It's like it was a
risky book to write.

00:44:03.340 --> 00:44:04.450 align:middle line:90%
Because I can't--

00:44:04.450 --> 00:44:07.060 align:middle line:84%
I don't have any solid
scientific foundation.

00:44:07.060 --> 00:44:08.568 align:middle line:90%
So here's evidence based.

00:44:08.568 --> 00:44:10.360 align:middle line:84%
We can tell you the
studies that were done.

00:44:10.360 --> 00:44:12.090 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: You're not
a numerologist.

00:44:12.090 --> 00:44:13.210 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLMAN: No, I'm not.

00:44:13.210 --> 00:44:16.330 align:middle line:84%
I was never very
interested in numerology.

00:44:16.330 --> 00:44:19.480 align:middle line:84%
Some of the books I looked
at seemed vague and abstract.

00:44:19.480 --> 00:44:21.260 align:middle line:90%
Maybe 40% accurate.

00:44:21.260 --> 00:44:23.093 align:middle line:84%
But this book hits
people over the head in--

00:44:23.093 --> 00:44:23.893 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:44:23.893 --> 00:44:25.930 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: --the work
I did, putting into it.

00:44:25.930 --> 00:44:28.878 align:middle line:84%
Jack London said it takes hard
writing to make easy reading.

00:44:28.878 --> 00:44:30.670 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Yes, you have
to put a lot into it.

00:44:30.670 --> 00:44:31.690 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: I put
it in the writing.

00:44:31.690 --> 00:44:33.250 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: But what's
the theme here?

00:44:33.250 --> 00:44:35.950 align:middle line:84%
With all of your work
and with this show

00:44:35.950 --> 00:44:37.950 align:middle line:90%
is about that word purpose.

00:44:37.950 --> 00:44:38.750 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLMAN: Right.

00:44:38.750 --> 00:44:39.790 align:middle line:90%
Well, yeah.

00:44:39.790 --> 00:44:41.590 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It's such a thing.

00:44:41.590 --> 00:44:45.250 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: People who--
functioning well in life

00:44:45.250 --> 00:44:47.650 align:middle line:84%
doesn't sound too
sexy or spiritual.

00:44:47.650 --> 00:44:49.930 align:middle line:84%
But those who do
get things done tend

00:44:49.930 --> 00:44:51.805 align:middle line:84%
to be-- have a baseline
of more satisfaction

00:44:51.805 --> 00:44:53.980 align:middle line:84%
and fulfillment in
life than people

00:44:53.980 --> 00:44:55.450 align:middle line:90%
who don't get things done.

00:44:55.450 --> 00:44:57.250 align:middle line:90%
So part of my work is practical.

00:44:57.250 --> 00:45:00.940 align:middle line:84%
It helps people to take
action in their life.

00:45:00.940 --> 00:45:03.370 align:middle line:84%
That's another thing,
rather than necessarily

00:45:03.370 --> 00:45:05.530 align:middle line:84%
trying to fix our
insides, so we can

00:45:05.530 --> 00:45:07.420 align:middle line:84%
have just the right,
positive thoughts

00:45:07.420 --> 00:45:11.150 align:middle line:84%
and feel just the right
emotions, rather than that--

00:45:11.150 --> 00:45:13.060 align:middle line:84%
for example, I say
to people, I don't

00:45:13.060 --> 00:45:15.910 align:middle line:84%
recommend that you feel
grateful, or happy,

00:45:15.910 --> 00:45:18.400 align:middle line:90%
or peaceful, or kind, or loving.

00:45:18.400 --> 00:45:20.410 align:middle line:84%
I recommend you
bring that into life.

00:45:20.410 --> 00:45:21.880 align:middle line:90%
Behave that way.

00:45:21.880 --> 00:45:23.500 align:middle line:90%
Behave with gratitude.

00:45:23.500 --> 00:45:24.640 align:middle line:90%
Say thank you to people.

00:45:24.640 --> 00:45:25.780 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Don't just feel it.

00:45:25.780 --> 00:45:28.060 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: It's because we
have less control over what

00:45:28.060 --> 00:45:29.478 align:middle line:90%
feelings come to pass.

00:45:29.478 --> 00:45:32.020 align:middle line:84%
How many of us have received a
gift and we didn't necessarily

00:45:32.020 --> 00:45:33.490 align:middle line:90%
feel grateful?

00:45:33.490 --> 00:45:34.360 align:middle line:90%
So we--

00:45:34.360 --> 00:45:34.750 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:45:34.750 --> 00:45:36.792 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: --have less
control over what feelings

00:45:36.792 --> 00:45:40.600 align:middle line:84%
pass through us like the weather
than we do-- what we actually

00:45:40.600 --> 00:45:42.110 align:middle line:90%
do moment to moment.

00:45:42.110 --> 00:45:44.920 align:middle line:84%
So this way of action is
another fundamental element

00:45:44.920 --> 00:45:46.600 align:middle line:90%
of this approach to living.

00:45:46.600 --> 00:45:48.910 align:middle line:84%
And I help people to
take practical action,

00:45:48.910 --> 00:45:51.853 align:middle line:84%
small steps that can make
a very big difference.

00:45:51.853 --> 00:45:53.020 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It's so interesting.

00:45:53.020 --> 00:45:55.810 align:middle line:84%
Because your work is you
didn't do this to create

00:45:55.810 --> 00:45:57.670 align:middle line:90%
a brand like people can do.

00:45:57.670 --> 00:46:00.802 align:middle line:84%
And I want to
create a brand of--

00:46:00.802 --> 00:46:03.960 align:middle line:84%
you're shaking your
head like, heck no.

00:46:03.960 --> 00:46:06.280 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: All I know is I
say it was not strategic.

00:46:06.280 --> 00:46:07.330 align:middle line:90%
If it were, I'd say that.

00:46:07.330 --> 00:46:09.280 align:middle line:90%
Yes, I formed a clear strategy.

00:46:09.280 --> 00:46:12.050 align:middle line:84%
But, no, I just opened my
heart, opened my mouth.

00:46:12.050 --> 00:46:13.425 align:middle line:84%
And that's how I
write and speak.

00:46:13.425 --> 00:46:15.973 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: But it's cool because
it created its own brand.

00:46:15.973 --> 00:46:17.140 align:middle line:90%
Peaceful Warrior created it.

00:46:17.140 --> 00:46:18.360 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: Yeah, now
it's become that.

00:46:18.360 --> 00:46:19.010 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:46:19.010 --> 00:46:19.470 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:46:19.470 --> 00:46:20.390 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It did.

00:46:20.390 --> 00:46:22.780 align:middle line:84%
And would you say
that it's a brand that

00:46:22.780 --> 00:46:26.510 align:middle line:84%
identifies with people finding
their path, finding their--

00:46:26.510 --> 00:46:27.310 align:middle line:90%
yeah, I read that.

00:46:27.310 --> 00:46:30.190 align:middle line:84%
And it's a community that
it creates amongst people.

00:46:30.190 --> 00:46:32.470 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: I think there's
something about the term.

00:46:32.470 --> 00:46:35.200 align:middle line:84%
For 30 years, the
seminars I've taught,

00:46:35.200 --> 00:46:38.470 align:middle line:84%
workshops wherever
I teach, about 50%

00:46:38.470 --> 00:46:41.770 align:middle line:84%
of the people in the audience
are male and about 50 female.

00:46:41.770 --> 00:46:43.600 align:middle line:84%
But the point is
there's a balance there.

00:46:43.600 --> 00:46:45.610 align:middle line:84%
Because everybody
I know is striving

00:46:45.610 --> 00:46:48.610 align:middle line:84%
to live with a peaceful heart,
but recognizes there are

00:46:48.610 --> 00:46:51.490 align:middle line:90%
times we need a warrior spirit.

00:46:51.490 --> 00:46:54.520 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Yeah, well sometimes
I'm too much warrior.

00:46:54.520 --> 00:46:57.310 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes I really
use too much will

00:46:57.310 --> 00:46:58.510 align:middle line:90%
to get something to happen.

00:46:58.510 --> 00:46:59.970 align:middle line:90%
And it comes with an edge.

00:46:59.970 --> 00:47:01.960 align:middle line:84%
It comes at a little
bit of an edge--

00:47:01.960 --> 00:47:02.813 align:middle line:90%
a lot of it.

00:47:02.813 --> 00:47:05.230 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: There's a game we
play in some of my workshops.

00:47:05.230 --> 00:47:06.030 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, good.

00:47:06.030 --> 00:47:07.690 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: We do a
hand-clapping game.

00:47:07.690 --> 00:47:11.600 align:middle line:84%
And we learn to assert
ourselves in the right moments,

00:47:11.600 --> 00:47:12.400 align:middle line:90%
but also--

00:47:12.400 --> 00:47:12.830 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Can we do it?

00:47:12.830 --> 00:47:13.913 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLMAN: Well, we could.

00:47:13.913 --> 00:47:16.030 align:middle line:84%
I mean, yeah, we can
try it sitting down.

00:47:16.030 --> 00:47:18.085 align:middle line:84%
The idea is to see if
you can get your partner

00:47:18.085 --> 00:47:20.290 align:middle line:90%
a little off balance.

00:47:20.290 --> 00:47:22.480 align:middle line:84%
And so if I'm
tense, for example,

00:47:22.480 --> 00:47:23.885 align:middle line:90%
you do a really assertive push.

00:47:23.885 --> 00:47:25.010 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: First, towards you.

00:47:25.010 --> 00:47:26.593 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: Then I
can get off balance.

00:47:26.593 --> 00:47:30.760 align:middle line:84%
OK, but if I also
know how to receive,

00:47:30.760 --> 00:47:32.500 align:middle line:90%
and take in, and relax.

00:47:32.500 --> 00:47:35.200 align:middle line:84%
Then if you push, there's
nothing to push against.

00:47:35.200 --> 00:47:38.860 align:middle line:84%
It's like push hands in tai chi,
but it's a very accessible way.

00:47:38.860 --> 00:47:41.735 align:middle line:84%
So you learn there are times
in life to assert yourself.

00:47:41.735 --> 00:47:45.070 align:middle line:84%
And there are other times
to receive, and listen,

00:47:45.070 --> 00:47:46.270 align:middle line:90%
and open up.

00:47:46.270 --> 00:47:48.400 align:middle line:84%
So it helps us
balance our character.

00:47:48.400 --> 00:47:50.530 align:middle line:84%
Rather than being the
good girl or the nice boy

00:47:50.530 --> 00:47:54.310 align:middle line:84%
all the time, there are times
we want to really be forthright.

00:47:54.310 --> 00:47:57.430 align:middle line:84%
But other times-- sit,
and listen, and take in.

00:47:57.430 --> 00:48:00.280 align:middle line:84%
So we have trouble
with one or the other.

00:48:00.280 --> 00:48:02.320 align:middle line:84%
And this brings us
back into balance.

00:48:02.320 --> 00:48:05.800 align:middle line:84%
One of the first laws in my
book, the laws of spirit,

00:48:05.800 --> 00:48:09.670 align:middle line:84%
is about the law of balance,
not overdoing or underdoing.

00:48:09.670 --> 00:48:11.470 align:middle line:90%
It's a constant challenge.

00:48:11.470 --> 00:48:15.280 align:middle line:84%
When I go to the Y to work
out, how hard do I push?

00:48:15.280 --> 00:48:17.500 align:middle line:84%
Do I push so hard that
I get great results,

00:48:17.500 --> 00:48:20.605 align:middle line:84%
but I wake up in the morning
going, oh, here comes workout?

00:48:20.605 --> 00:48:25.870 align:middle line:84%
Or how do I find the balance
where I can enjoy it, but also

00:48:25.870 --> 00:48:26.670 align:middle line:90%
get some results?

00:48:26.670 --> 00:48:29.410 align:middle line:84%
So balance in every
aspect of life

00:48:29.410 --> 00:48:31.225 align:middle line:84%
is a quality we can
all benefit from.

00:48:31.225 --> 00:48:32.350 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's a tough one.

00:48:32.350 --> 00:48:35.740 align:middle line:84%
Because I've heard there is
no such thing as balance.

00:48:35.740 --> 00:48:38.610 align:middle line:84%
You're really never right
on the balance beam.

00:48:38.610 --> 00:48:40.960 align:middle line:84%
You're usually on
either side of it.

00:48:40.960 --> 00:48:42.170 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLMAN: Yes.

00:48:42.170 --> 00:48:45.293 align:middle line:84%
Gymnasts-- first, they
begin, and they fall off.

00:48:45.293 --> 00:48:47.210 align:middle line:84%
But as they get better,
they get more refined.

00:48:47.210 --> 00:48:48.770 align:middle line:90%
And they have a little bobble.

00:48:48.770 --> 00:48:52.640 align:middle line:84%
So there's nothing like
perfect balance, because moment

00:48:52.640 --> 00:48:53.690 align:middle line:90%
to moment.

00:48:53.690 --> 00:48:56.000 align:middle line:84%
And there's no such thing
as balanced exercises.

00:48:56.000 --> 00:48:58.388 align:middle line:84%
What is balanced
exercise for an Olympian

00:48:58.388 --> 00:49:00.680 align:middle line:84%
may be different from somebody
who's a beginner or just

00:49:00.680 --> 00:49:01.910 align:middle line:90%
rehabilitating.

00:49:01.910 --> 00:49:04.370 align:middle line:84%
So we all have to find
our own balance of what

00:49:04.370 --> 00:49:07.130 align:middle line:90%
works for us day to day.

00:49:07.130 --> 00:49:09.380 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, this is
a good-- great example

00:49:09.380 --> 00:49:11.040 align:middle line:90%
of on and off balance.

00:49:11.040 --> 00:49:12.772 align:middle line:84%
We're going to take
a look here at Dan

00:49:12.772 --> 00:49:15.230 align:middle line:84%
showing another example from
the book, "The Hidden School."

00:49:15.230 --> 00:49:16.030 align:middle line:90%
Take a look.

00:49:16.030 --> 00:49:24.190 align:middle line:90%


00:49:24.190 --> 00:49:26.560 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: Not long after
I met my old mentor, who

00:49:26.560 --> 00:49:29.290 align:middle line:84%
I named Socrates, he
gave me a business card

00:49:29.290 --> 00:49:33.670 align:middle line:84%
with three words--
paradox, humor, and change.

00:49:33.670 --> 00:49:37.210 align:middle line:84%
These words, these ideas
appear again and again

00:49:37.210 --> 00:49:38.590 align:middle line:90%
in "The Hidden School."

00:49:38.590 --> 00:49:40.690 align:middle line:84%
In reading the saga,
reading the adventure,

00:49:40.690 --> 00:49:42.130 align:middle line:84%
there are many
humorous incidents

00:49:42.130 --> 00:49:45.910 align:middle line:84%
that happened that remind
us cosmic sense of humor

00:49:45.910 --> 00:49:49.690 align:middle line:84%
can be very, very useful in
approaching the challenges

00:49:49.690 --> 00:49:51.520 align:middle line:90%
of everyday life.

00:49:51.520 --> 00:49:56.110 align:middle line:84%
And change-- well, I
have radical changes

00:49:56.110 --> 00:49:59.530 align:middle line:84%
demanded of me by
page 2 in the new book

00:49:59.530 --> 00:50:01.600 align:middle line:90%
and throughout the book.

00:50:01.600 --> 00:50:04.930 align:middle line:84%
Not predictable,
but change happens.

00:50:04.930 --> 00:50:09.400 align:middle line:84%
But I think the most important
point in "The Hidden School"

00:50:09.400 --> 00:50:11.860 align:middle line:90%
revolves around paradox.

00:50:11.860 --> 00:50:14.755 align:middle line:84%
Paradox, the reader
will learn, is

00:50:14.755 --> 00:50:18.880 align:middle line:84%
a key to understanding some
of the major questions of life

00:50:18.880 --> 00:50:24.430 align:middle line:84%
about big issues like free
will, and time, and death,

00:50:24.430 --> 00:50:28.180 align:middle line:84%
and whether we're all one or
whether we're separate beings.

00:50:28.180 --> 00:50:32.470 align:middle line:84%
So understanding paradox is
a key and a recurring theme

00:50:32.470 --> 00:50:34.150 align:middle line:90%
throughout "The Hidden School."

00:50:34.150 --> 00:50:36.490 align:middle line:84%
This approach to
living is not so

00:50:36.490 --> 00:50:40.120 align:middle line:84%
much about fixing our insides,
so that we can go out and live.

00:50:40.120 --> 00:50:42.760 align:middle line:84%
It's not about having
perfect, positive thoughts

00:50:42.760 --> 00:50:44.770 align:middle line:90%
or an entirely quiet mind.

00:50:44.770 --> 00:50:47.980 align:middle line:84%
It's not about having
the right emotions,

00:50:47.980 --> 00:50:49.600 align:middle line:90%
so we can go out and live well.

00:50:49.600 --> 00:50:55.180 align:middle line:84%
Rather, it focuses on action,
our response to each moment.

00:50:55.180 --> 00:50:57.340 align:middle line:84%
Because most of us
looking back will

00:50:57.340 --> 00:50:59.260 align:middle line:84%
see that our lives
have been shaped

00:50:59.260 --> 00:51:01.735 align:middle line:84%
by what we have done
moment to moment,

00:51:01.735 --> 00:51:03.610 align:middle line:84%
not just what we've been
thinking or feeling.

00:51:03.610 --> 00:51:06.240 align:middle line:90%


00:51:06.240 --> 00:51:09.420 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Humor-- how
important it is.

00:51:09.420 --> 00:51:11.340 align:middle line:84%
I mean, it is just
because we have

00:51:11.340 --> 00:51:13.450 align:middle line:84%
to be able to not take
ourselves too seriously.

00:51:13.450 --> 00:51:14.250 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLMAN: Yes.

00:51:14.250 --> 00:51:15.667 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It really
gets in the way.

00:51:15.667 --> 00:51:16.470 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLMAN: Yes.

00:51:16.470 --> 00:51:18.930 align:middle line:84%
And by humor, it's not just
about laughing or telling

00:51:18.930 --> 00:51:19.360 align:middle line:90%
jokes.

00:51:19.360 --> 00:51:20.160 align:middle line:90%
That's wonderful.

00:51:20.160 --> 00:51:22.320 align:middle line:90%
It's a tension release.

00:51:22.320 --> 00:51:24.530 align:middle line:84%
But it's more about a
non-serious approach,

00:51:24.530 --> 00:51:26.640 align:middle line:84%
not taking ourselves
so seriously.

00:51:26.640 --> 00:51:29.370 align:middle line:84%
This character Dan Millman
has a lot of quirks,

00:51:29.370 --> 00:51:31.680 align:middle line:84%
and he's just doing
his best in life.

00:51:31.680 --> 00:51:34.260 align:middle line:84%
So I don't take myself
so seriously anymore.

00:51:34.260 --> 00:51:36.660 align:middle line:84%
I take my work
seriously, I guess.

00:51:36.660 --> 00:51:39.400 align:middle line:84%
So it's more of a
cosmic sense of humor.

00:51:39.400 --> 00:51:40.500 align:middle line:90%
I remember a cartoon.

00:51:40.500 --> 00:51:42.960 align:middle line:84%
And it showed two men
up on a dungeon wall--

00:51:42.960 --> 00:51:44.150 align:middle line:90%
long beards.

00:51:44.150 --> 00:51:46.560 align:middle line:84%
They're shackled by
their arms and legs.

00:51:46.560 --> 00:51:48.300 align:middle line:84%
And one turns to
the other and says,

00:51:48.300 --> 00:51:50.820 align:middle line:90%
psst, now, here's my plan.

00:51:50.820 --> 00:51:52.440 align:middle line:84%
I mean, that's human
spirit, isn't it?

00:51:52.440 --> 00:51:52.920 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:51:52.920 --> 00:51:54.540 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: That's
the human spirit.

00:51:54.540 --> 00:51:56.100 align:middle line:90%
Now, here's my plan.

00:51:56.100 --> 00:51:57.990 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, you
have grandchildren.

00:51:57.990 --> 00:52:01.050 align:middle line:84%
And you can't really
but laugh and giggle

00:52:01.050 --> 00:52:02.342 align:middle line:90%
when you're around them, right?

00:52:02.342 --> 00:52:03.758 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: They're
great teachers.

00:52:03.758 --> 00:52:05.680 align:middle line:84%
We all know children
can be great teachers.

00:52:05.680 --> 00:52:06.630 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Young, too.

00:52:06.630 --> 00:52:07.650 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:52:07.650 --> 00:52:10.290 align:middle line:84%
Well, now, if you were to
look back and find out,

00:52:10.290 --> 00:52:12.720 align:middle line:84%
what is the massive
purpose here?

00:52:12.720 --> 00:52:15.930 align:middle line:84%
What is your biggest why as
to the reason that you've

00:52:15.930 --> 00:52:18.750 align:middle line:84%
written all these books
and everything that you're

00:52:18.750 --> 00:52:20.160 align:middle line:90%
teaching?

00:52:20.160 --> 00:52:21.000 align:middle line:90%
Why do you do this?

00:52:21.000 --> 00:52:22.500 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: I can
say with confidence

00:52:22.500 --> 00:52:23.940 align:middle line:90%
I haven't the faintest idea.

00:52:23.940 --> 00:52:25.080 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:52:25.080 --> 00:52:27.300 align:middle line:84%
Life remains a
mystery to me, Lisa.

00:52:27.300 --> 00:52:28.100 align:middle line:90%
It really does.

00:52:28.100 --> 00:52:30.017 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That's the first
time I've heard that.

00:52:30.017 --> 00:52:30.870 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:52:30.870 --> 00:52:31.680 align:middle line:90%
I love it.

00:52:31.680 --> 00:52:33.138 align:middle line:84%
People usually come
with this deep,

00:52:33.138 --> 00:52:35.280 align:middle line:84%
meaningful-- you're
like, no clue.

00:52:35.280 --> 00:52:36.780 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLMAN: No, it's a mystery.

00:52:36.780 --> 00:52:38.580 align:middle line:90%
I just do what I do.

00:52:38.580 --> 00:52:41.670 align:middle line:84%
I believe we're hardwired
to be who we are.

00:52:41.670 --> 00:52:44.280 align:middle line:84%
And so I'm just continuing
along that path,

00:52:44.280 --> 00:52:45.900 align:middle line:90%
trusting along the way.

00:52:45.900 --> 00:52:48.090 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So then, how do
you know what's next?

00:52:48.090 --> 00:52:49.490 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLMAN: It'll appear.

00:52:49.490 --> 00:52:51.660 align:middle line:90%
And then I respond to it.

00:52:51.660 --> 00:52:53.100 align:middle line:90%
It may appear inside.

00:52:53.100 --> 00:52:56.700 align:middle line:90%
It may be a movement in me.

00:52:56.700 --> 00:53:01.320 align:middle line:84%
But I just wait, and watch,
and stay open to opportunities

00:53:01.320 --> 00:53:02.550 align:middle line:90%
as they occur.

00:53:02.550 --> 00:53:05.305 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: But you do also have
a goal in mind, don't you?

00:53:05.305 --> 00:53:06.105 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLMAN: Yes.

00:53:06.105 --> 00:53:06.905 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:53:06.905 --> 00:53:09.300 align:middle line:84%
But only-- maybe it's become
more short-term goals.

00:53:09.300 --> 00:53:11.230 align:middle line:90%
What in the moment can I do?

00:53:11.230 --> 00:53:14.010 align:middle line:90%
What is my purpose now?

00:53:14.010 --> 00:53:19.200 align:middle line:84%
When I walk out of here, when
I do something to meet friends

00:53:19.200 --> 00:53:21.480 align:middle line:84%
tonight, I'll have
a different purpose.

00:53:21.480 --> 00:53:25.530 align:middle line:84%
But overall, I seem to
have found a particular joy

00:53:25.530 --> 00:53:28.350 align:middle line:90%
in sharing in my own way.

00:53:28.350 --> 00:53:30.280 align:middle line:84%
Other people, also,
are called to do that.

00:53:30.280 --> 00:53:31.620 align:middle line:90%
And I encourage them.

00:53:31.620 --> 00:53:33.630 align:middle line:84%
My daughter and I wrote
a writing book together

00:53:33.630 --> 00:53:35.430 align:middle line:84%
called "The Creative
Compass," where

00:53:35.430 --> 00:53:40.150 align:middle line:84%
we encourage people to follow
their own creative impulses

00:53:40.150 --> 00:53:40.950 align:middle line:90%
in writing.

00:53:40.950 --> 00:53:44.350 align:middle line:84%
So it's really not so
much about me anymore.

00:53:44.350 --> 00:53:47.550 align:middle line:84%
It's about, what can I
do to touch other lives?

00:53:47.550 --> 00:53:50.490 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Do you ever
wonder about retirement?

00:53:50.490 --> 00:53:52.950 align:middle line:84%
Or what's your plan
for the future?

00:53:52.950 --> 00:53:55.173 align:middle line:84%
I mean, does that
ever cross your mind?

00:53:55.173 --> 00:53:56.090 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLMAN: Not really.

00:53:56.090 --> 00:53:56.490 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Really?

00:53:56.490 --> 00:53:57.290 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLMAN: No.

00:53:57.290 --> 00:53:58.980 align:middle line:90%
Some people that works for.

00:53:58.980 --> 00:54:00.090 align:middle line:90%
But you know the saying.

00:54:00.090 --> 00:54:01.595 align:middle line:90%
It's been repeated many times.

00:54:01.595 --> 00:54:03.720 align:middle line:84%
If you want to make God
laugh, tell God your plans.

00:54:03.720 --> 00:54:04.890 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah, that's true.

00:54:04.890 --> 00:54:06.750 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLMAN: Plans change.

00:54:06.750 --> 00:54:10.770 align:middle line:84%
So I find short-term goals
are more realistic, usually

00:54:10.770 --> 00:54:14.110 align:middle line:84%
by definition than
making a long-term goal.

00:54:14.110 --> 00:54:15.720 align:middle line:84%
But again, any
goal can be useful,

00:54:15.720 --> 00:54:19.260 align:middle line:90%
because it gives us a direction.

00:54:19.260 --> 00:54:21.600 align:middle line:84%
And I think that's
always useful.

00:54:21.600 --> 00:54:23.490 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, your
short-term goal of health

00:54:23.490 --> 00:54:25.570 align:middle line:90%
is working for you.

00:54:25.570 --> 00:54:26.370 align:middle line:90%
>>MILLMAN: Yeah.

00:54:26.370 --> 00:54:27.170 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:54:27.170 --> 00:54:28.710 align:middle line:90%
But I'll grow old, too.

00:54:28.710 --> 00:54:30.090 align:middle line:90%
And we're like old cars.

00:54:30.090 --> 00:54:31.535 align:middle line:90%
You need tune-ups now and then.

00:54:31.535 --> 00:54:35.960 align:middle line:84%
And everybody has
their own challenges.

00:54:35.960 --> 00:54:36.960 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: I mean, I love--

00:54:36.960 --> 00:54:39.150 align:middle line:84%
can you tell us about your
daily exercise routine

00:54:39.150 --> 00:54:41.403 align:middle line:90%
now, still at 73?

00:54:41.403 --> 00:54:43.320 align:middle line:84%
>>MILLMAN: Well, I start
early in the morning.

00:54:43.320 --> 00:54:45.570 align:middle line:10%
As soon as I get up,
I do various exercises

00:54:45.570 --> 00:54:46.770 align:middle line:10%
that I've learned--

00:54:46.770 --> 00:54:48.900 align:middle line:10%
my Peaceful Warrior Workout,
but also, some of them

00:54:48.900 --> 00:54:53.160 align:middle line:10%
look like physical therapy
to help different liabilities

00:54:53.160 --> 00:54:56.650 align:middle line:10%
I've developed from all the
pounding I did in gymnastics.

00:54:56.650 --> 00:55:00.050 align:middle line:84%
And, yeah, I found some friends
at the Y. I go to a gym,

00:55:00.050 --> 00:55:01.410 align:middle line:90%
and we work out a little bit.

00:55:01.410 --> 00:55:05.070 align:middle line:84%
But everything can be done
at home on one's carpet

00:55:05.070 --> 00:55:05.980 align:middle line:90%
using body weight.

00:55:05.980 --> 00:55:08.190 align:middle line:84%
It's a great, very
natural way to exercise.

00:55:08.190 --> 00:55:12.200 align:middle line:84%
But when someone says, I want
to be fit, you have to ask,

00:55:12.200 --> 00:55:13.000 align:middle line:90%
fit for what?

00:55:13.000 --> 00:55:14.730 align:middle line:90%
Do you want to run a triathlon?

00:55:14.730 --> 00:55:16.680 align:middle line:84%
Or do you want to be
able to walk upstairs

00:55:16.680 --> 00:55:18.090 align:middle line:90%
without getting winded?

00:55:18.090 --> 00:55:23.130 align:middle line:84%
So it's an individual choice
of what kind-- what we do,

00:55:23.130 --> 00:55:25.920 align:middle line:84%
and what fits our body, and
our mind, and our emotions,

00:55:25.920 --> 00:55:27.660 align:middle line:90%
and what we can sustain.

00:55:27.660 --> 00:55:30.420 align:middle line:84%
No matter how fit we
get in a boot camp--

00:55:30.420 --> 00:55:33.750 align:middle line:84%
unless you sustain that level,
you don't stay that fit.

00:55:33.750 --> 00:55:37.360 align:middle line:84%
So it's, what simple things
can we do day to day?

00:55:37.360 --> 00:55:40.380 align:middle line:84%
That's why I like
short-term, minimal things

00:55:40.380 --> 00:55:41.580 align:middle line:90%
we get done every day.

00:55:41.580 --> 00:55:43.693 align:middle line:90%
And we start the day right.

00:55:43.693 --> 00:55:44.860 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: And also, community.

00:55:44.860 --> 00:55:45.840 align:middle line:90%
You mentioned that.

00:55:45.840 --> 00:55:49.355 align:middle line:84%
You mentioned meeting people and
doing community-like exercise.

00:55:49.355 --> 00:55:51.230 align:middle line:10%
>>MILLMAN: Well, in the
spiritual traditions,

00:55:51.230 --> 00:55:52.990 align:middle line:10%
there is the Buddha
or the teacher.

00:55:52.990 --> 00:55:54.640 align:middle line:10%
And we all have
different teachers.

00:55:54.640 --> 00:55:56.120 align:middle line:10%
There is the teaching--

00:55:56.120 --> 00:56:00.270 align:middle line:10%
the Dharma, and then the
Sangha, or the community.

00:56:00.270 --> 00:56:02.530 align:middle line:90%
And so it's very useful.

00:56:02.530 --> 00:56:04.110 align:middle line:84%
We've all read about
how people tend

00:56:04.110 --> 00:56:06.540 align:middle line:84%
to live longer if they have
connections with family,

